%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20rivals%20that%20could%20hammer%20away%20at%20the%20chip%20company's%20dominance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hchowdhury%40insider.com%20(Hasan%20Chowdhury)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-predicts-chip-shortage-nvidia-ease-next-year-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC's%20Marriage%20Equality%20Judgment%3A%20Manufactured%20Classifications%20and%20Return%20of%20'Minuscule%20Minorities'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20delivered%20its%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2022%2F36593%2F36593_2022_1_1501_47792_Judgement_17-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESupriyo%20%40%20Supriya%20Chakraborty%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20recognise%20same-sex%20marriage%2C%20I%20have%20argued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F10%2F21%2Fthe-supreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgment-i-on-the-right-to-marry-and-a-case-of-abstention-through-delegitimisation-guest-post%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20best%20understood%20as%20the%20justification%20of%20institutional%20abstention%20through%20delegitimising%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20case.%20This%20delegitimisation%2C%20I%20have%20argued%2C%20occurred%20through%20three%20means%3A%20the%20denial%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20constitutional%20right%20to%20marry%3B%20a%20misidentification%20of%20the%20classification%E2%80%99s%20subject-matter%3B%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20artificial%20barriers%20in%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20transform%20social%20structures.%20I%20have%20covered%20the%20first%20of%20these%20means%20%E2%80%93%20the%20denial%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20%E2%80%93%20in%20my%20previous%20post.%20The%20third%20means%2C%20which%20concerned%20the%20creation%20of%20artificial%20barriers%20to%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20remedy%20rights%20violations%2C%20has%20been%20discussed%20by%20Hardik%20Choubey%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F11%2F08%2Fthe-supreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgment-v-on-discrimination-judicial-remedies-and-judicial-abnegation-guest-post%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20piece%2C%20I%20examine%20the%20second%20mode%20through%20which%20the%20court%20justified%20its%20institutional%20abstention%2C%20which%20concerned%20its%20response%20to%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20claims%20under%20Article%2014.%20While%20the%20petitioners%20proposed%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15480%2F1%2Fspecial_marriage_act.pdf%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99s%20(%E2%80%9CSMA%E2%80%9D)%20heteronormative%20conceptualisation%20of%20marriage%20caused%20the%20exclusion%20of%20persons%20who%20could%20not%20%E2%80%93%20due%20to%20ascriptive%20factors%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%93%20enter%20into%20such%20marriages%20and%20enjoy%20the%20bundle%20of%20rights%20they%20confer%2C%20the%20court%20rejected%20this%20claim%20at%20its%20very%20inception.%20It%20held%20that%20there%20was%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20no%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20forms%20of%20marriage%20caused%20by%20the%20SMA%20because%20Parliament%20%E2%80%93%20let%20alone%20consciously%20excluding%20such%20marriage%20%E2%80%93%20was%20not%20even%20%3Cem%3Eaware%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20its%20possible%20existence%20at%20the%20time%20of%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20enactment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20towards%20identifying%20exclusion%20that%20prizes%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20exclude%E2%80%9D%20over%20factual%2C%20verifiable%20exclusion%2C%20I%20propose%2C%20is%20a%20novel%20and%20dangerous%20development%20in%20constitutional%20doctrine%2C%20and%20was%20designedly%20deployed%20to%20delegitimise%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20Article%2014%20challenge.%20Further%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20Bhat%2C%20J.%2C%20in%20his%20Article%2014%20enquiry%2C%20commits%20a%20major%20misidentification%20of%20the%20classes%20the%20SMA%20creates%2C%20and%20creates%20diversions%20to%20circumvent%20a%20response%20to%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage.%20I%20make%20this%20argument%20in%20the%20following%20manner%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Efirst%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20discuss%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20Article%2014%20enquiry%20into%20the%20SMA%20and%20interrogate%20its%20major%20propositions%3B%20%3Cem%3Esecond%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20court%20invents%20a%20novel%20standard%20of%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20to%20determine%20a%20differentia%20under%20Article%2014%2C%20a%20dangerous%20development%20that%20risks%20a%20permanent%20entrenchment%20of%20regressive%20parliamentary%20actions%20based%20on%20a%20Court%E2%80%99s%20assessment%20of%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20epistemic%20limitations%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20enactment%3B%20and%20%3Cem%3Ethird%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20court%20substantially%20errs%20in%20identifying%20the%20classes%20the%20SMA%20creates%2C%20and%20circumvents%20a%20response%20to%20whether%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20of%20regulating%20%3Cem%3Eexclusively%3C%2Fem%3E%20heterosexual%20marriage%20continues%20to%20remain%20legitimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManipulating%20classifications%3A%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20treatment%20of%20equality%20and%20non-discrimination%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20impugning%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F594580%2F%5C%22%3ESection%204%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20petitioners%20made%20a%20very%20straightforward%20argument%3A%20it%20provides%20a%20set%20of%20conjunctive%20conditions%20to%20be%20fulfilled%20by%20a%20couple%20seeking%20a%20marriage%2C%20with%20sub-section%20(c)%20mandating%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmale%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfemale%E2%80%9D.%20This%20heteronormative%20prescription%20for%20marriage%20constitutes%20discrimination%20based%20on%20persons%E2%80%99%20sexual%20orientation.%20Sexual%20orientation%20is%20an%20ascriptive%20characteristic%20protected%20by%20Article%2015(1)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20as%20interpreted%20by%20Chandrachud%2C%20J.%20(as%20he%20then%20was)%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F168671544%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENavtej%20Johar%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Without%20prejudice%20to%20the%20challenge%20based%20on%20Article%2015(1)%2C%20the%20impugned%20section%20also%20creates%20a%20classification%20between%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20for%20availing%20marriage%2C%20with%20such%20classification%20having%20no%20nexus%20with%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20of%20providing%20a%20platform%20for%20the%20secular%20solemnization%20of%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhat%2C%20J.%2C%20speaking%20for%20the%20majority%2C%20follows%20the%20general%20tenor%20of%20delegitimization%20discernible%20in%20his%20treatment%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20making%20a%20similar%2C%20sweeping%20assertion%20here%20as%20well%3A%C2%A0he%20states%20that%20the%20SMA%2C%20instead%20of%20classifying%20between%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20%3Cem%3Eactually%3C%2Fem%3E%20classifies%20between%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%9D%20.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20from%20availing%20marriage%20was%20not%20a%20%3Cem%3Econscious%20parliamentary%20choice%3C%2Fem%3E%20made%20during%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20enactment%2C%20and%20was%2C%20instead%20caused%20by%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20epistemic%20limits%3A%20it%20could%20not%20have%20known%20that%20marriage%20can%20be%20conceptualized%20in%20any%20manner%20but%20heteronormatively.%20He%20provides%20evidence%20of%20such%20epistemic%20limits%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%20(%E2%80%9CIPC%E2%80%9D)%2C%20arguing%20that%20since%20even%20non-reproductive%20sexual%20intercourse%20constituted%20a%20penal%20offence%20at%20the%20time%20Parliament%20enacted%20the%20SMA%2C%20it%20could%20not%20have%20%3Cem%3Eimagined%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20theoretical%20possibility%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage.%20On%20this%20basis%2C%20since%20Parliament%20could%20not%20have%20%3Cem%3Eintended%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20classification%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20subsequent%20denial%20of%20marriage%20%E2%80%93%20based%20on%20sexual%20orientation%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20said%20that%20the%20SMA%20%3Cem%3Ein%20fact%3C%2Fem%3E%20classified%20between%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20for%20availing%20marriage%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20idea%20to%20exclude%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20because%20at%20that%20time%2C%20even%20consensual%20physical%20intimacy%20of%20such%20persons%2C%20was%20outlawed%20by%20Section%20377%20IPC.%20So%2C%20while%20the%20Act%20sought%20to%20provide%20an%20avenue%20for%20those%20marriages%20that%20did%20not%20enjoy%20support%20in%20society%2C%20or%20did%20not%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20custom%20to%20solemnise%2C%20it%20would%20be%20quite%20a%20stretch%20to%20say%20that%20this%20included%20same%20sex%20marriages.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20statute%2C%20must%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6The%20classification%20was%20primarily%20not%20between%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20but%20heterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20differentia%20itself%20does%20not%20concern%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20failure%20of%20the%20Article%2014%20challenge%20at%20its%20very%20first%20prong.%20Assuming%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20classification%20was%20based%20on%20sexual%20orientation%2C%20and%20was%20valid%20at%20the%20time%20it%20was%20made%20due%20to%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20rational%20nexus%20with%20its%20objective%20(of%20facilitating%20%3Cem%3Eonly%3C%2Fem%3E%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriage)%2C%20the%20next%20question%20was%20whether%2C%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20time%2C%20this%20classification%20lost%20its%20nexus%20with%20the%20original%20objective%2C%20or%20the%20original%20objective%20itself%20turned%20illegitimate.%20This%20is%20because%20an%20Article%2014%20enquiry%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0apart%20from%20examining%20the%20classification%20and%20its%20nexus%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0also%20asks%20whether%20the%20objective%20pursued%20by%20the%20classification%20may%20be%20deemed%20%E2%80%9Clegitimate%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhat%2C%20J.%2C%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20answering%20this%20question%20genuinely%2C%20manoeuvres%20his%20way%20out%20of%20it%20through%20a%20very%20peculiar%20framing%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0instead%20of%20asking%20whether%20the%20objective%20of%20securing%20a%20platform%20for%20the%20solemnization%20of%20%3Cem%3Eonly%20%3C%2Fem%3Eheterosexual%20marriages%20(at%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriages)%20has%20turned%20illegitimate%2C%20he%20asks%20whether%20the%20objective%20of%20facilitating%20inter-faith%20heterosexual%20marriages%20can%20still%20%E2%80%93%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20day%20and%20age%20%E2%80%93%20be%20deemed%20relevant.%20This%20question%2C%20though%20wholly%20disconnected%20from%20the%20question%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20validity%2C%20is%20answered%20in%20the%20affirmative%20to%20somehow%20sustain%20it%3A%20in%20other%20words%2C%20the%20continuing%20relevance%20of%20a%20platform%20to%20solemnize%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriage%20was%20invoked%20to%20justify%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrachud%2C%20CJ.%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20engages%20in%20no%20such%20intellectual%20gymnastics%2C%20holding%20straightforwardly%20that%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20incompetence%20to%20grant%20a%20suitable%20remedy%20for%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%20renders%20an%20attempt%20at%20discerning%20its%20validity%20%E2%80%9Cfutile%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20an%20exercise%20to%20determine%20whether%20the%20SMA%20is%20unconstitutional%20because%20of%20under-inclusivity%20would%20be%20futile%20because%20of%20the%20limitations%20of%20this%20Court%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20grant%20a%20remedy.%20Whether%20a%20change%20should%20be%20brought%20into%20the%20legislative%20regime%20of%20the%20SMA%20is%20for%20Parliament%20to%20determine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20based%20on%20his%20assessment%20of%20the%20degree%20of%20judicial%20intervention%20necessary%20to%20effectuate%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20he%20prefers%20abstention%20as%20the%20best%20option.%20Kaul%2C%20J.%2C%20who%20concurs%20with%20Chandrachud%2C%20CJ.%2C%20does%20choose%20to%20answer%20this%20%E2%80%9Cfutile%E2%80%9D%20question%2C%20holding%20that%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%20u%2Fs%20the%204%20of%20the%20SMA%20does%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20constitute%20a%20violation%20of%20Article%2014%20.%20He%20registers%20his%20disagreement%20with%20Bhat%2C%20J.%2C%20noting%20that%20his%20assessment%20of%20the%20legislative%20objective%2C%20such%20that%20the%20SMA%20aimed%20to%20provide%20a%20platform%20for%20the%20solemnization%20of%20%3Cem%3Eonly%3C%2Fem%3E%20heterosexual%20marriages%2C%20constituted%20a%20conflation%20of%20the%20classification%20and%20its%20objective%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EI%20respectfully%20disagree%20with%20my%20brother%20Justice%20Ravindra%20Bhat%2C%20that%20the%20sole%20intention%20of%20the%20SMA%20was%20to%20enable%20marriage%20of%20heterosexual%20couples%20exclusively.%20To%20my%20mind%2C%20the%20stated%20objective%20of%20the%20SMA%20was%20not%20to%20regulate%20marriages%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20sexual%20orientation.%20This%20cannot%20be%20so%20as%20it%20would%20amount%20to%20conflating%20the%20differentia%20with%20the%20object%20of%20the%20statute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20SMA%20%3Cem%3Epresently%3C%2Fem%3E%20regulates%20heterosexual%20marriages%20exclusively%20provides%20no%20hint%20to%20its%20legislative%20objective%2C%20for%20%E2%80%9Cwe%E2%80%A6act%20in%20ways%20that%20do%20not%E2%80%A6correspond%20to%20our%20intent%E2%80%9D.%20Further%2C%20assuming%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20identification%20of%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20as%20the%20exclusive%20regulation%20of%20inter-faith%20marriage%20to%20be%20correct%2C%20he%20notes%20that%20this%20objective%20diverged%20with%20the%20classification%2C%20and%20was%20not%20subserved%20by%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage.%20The%20final%20leg%20of%20his%20disagreement%20with%20Bhat%2C%20J.%20concerns%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20formalistic%20affirmation%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20constitutionality%20based%20only%20on%20intelligible%20differentia%20and%20rational%20nexus%2C%20without%20an%20enquiry%20into%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eobjective%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20exclusively%20regulating%20heterosexual%20marriage.%20The%20objective%20of%20the%20sole%20regulation%20of%20heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20Kaul%2C%20J.%20notes%2C%20must%20be%20a%20%3Cem%3Ecause%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20unconstitutionality%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20%3Cem%3Ejustification%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20sustain%20its%20validity.%20This%20is%20because%20exclusion%20based%20on%20sexual%20orientation%20%E2%80%93%20akin%20to%20discrimination%20based%20on%20%E2%80%9Csex%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20is%20prohibited%20under%20Article%2015(1)%2C%20and%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20legitimate%20state%20objective.%20Ultimately%2C%20however%2C%20even%20Kaul%20J.%20notes%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cspider%E2%80%99s%20web%E2%80%9D%20of%20legislation%20would%20be%20disrupted%20if%20the%20Court%20tinkers%20with%20the%20SMA%2C%20and%20the%20consideration%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%20trumps%20that%20of%20rights-violation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20disagreements%20expressed%20in%20Kaul%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20dissent%2C%20the%20following%20propositions%20emerge%20from%20the%20majority%20opinion%3A%20%3Cem%3Efirst%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0which%20can%20be%20discerned%20from%20a%20study%20of%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20imaginative%20limitations%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20enactment%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0is%20a%20factor%20in%20determining%20a%20classification%E2%80%99s%20subject-matter%3B%20%3Cem%3Esecond%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20classification%20may%20not%20express%20a%20relationship%20between%20an%20included%20and%20excluded%20group%2C%20and%20can%2C%20instead%2C%20be%20defined%20in%20reference%20only%20to%20the%20included%20group%3B%20and%20%3Cem%3Ethird%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20classification%E2%80%99s%20pursuit%20of%20a%20constitutionally%20incompatible%20(and%20morally%20repugnant)%20objective%20is%20acceptable%2C%20and%20can%20be%20invoked%20to%20sustain%20its%20validity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20regressive%20invention%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20classification%2C%20as%20is%20traditionally%20understood%2C%20concerns%20the%20creation%20of%20real%20and%20tangible%20groups%2C%20on%20whom%20different%20legal%20standards%20apply.%20It%20arises%20in%20multiple%20ways%20%E2%80%93%20a%20distinct%20legal%20regime%20may%20be%20created%20to%20govern%20a%20group%20exclusively%20(this%20includes%20all%20kinds%20of%20codified%20personal%20law%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201955%3B%20specific%20provisions%20may%20be%20created%20to%20determine%20a%20group%E2%80%99s%20rights%20Section%20118%20of%20the%20Indian%20Succession%20Act%2C%201925%3B%20or%20restrictions%20may%20be%20levied%20on%20groups%E2%80%99%20exercise%20of%20their%20pre-existing%20rights%20Section%2016%20of%20the%20Orissa%20Municipal%20Act%2C%201950.%20A%20classification%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20distinguishing%20between%20groups%20to%20whom%20distinct%20legal%20standards%20apply%2C%20need%20not%20be%20made%20legislatively%20explicit%2C%20and%20can%20arise%20as%20a%20natural%20corollary%20to%20the%20inclusion%20of%20a%20single%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20identification%20of%20a%20differentia%20is%20a%20largely%20objective%20enquiry%2C%20and%20requires%20the%20demonstration%20of%20concrete%20groups%20being%20created%20through%20legislation.%20In%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F845216%2F%5C%22%3EAnuj%20Garg%20v.%20Hotel%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20example%2C%20Section%2030%20of%20the%20Punjab%20Excise%20Act%2C%201914%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0which%20prohibited%20women%20from%20being%20employed%20by%20establishments%20serving%20liquor%20%E2%80%93%20was%20challenged%20under%20Articles%2014%20and%2015.%20In%20case%20the%20Court%20employed%20%3Cem%3ESupriyo%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20logic%20of%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20could%20have%20held%20that%20at%20the%20time%20of%20enactment%2C%20Parliament%20could%20never%20have%20envisioned%20the%20possibility%20of%20women%20working%20in%20liquor%20establishments%2C%20and%20never%20intended%20to%20consciously%20exclude%20them%20from%20such%20employment%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20meant%20that%20Section%2030%20did%20not%20classify%20between%20%E2%80%9Cmen%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwomen%E2%80%9D.%20It%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20choose%20this%20path%2C%20noting%20straightforwardly%20the%20existence%20of%20such%20classification%2C%20enquiring%20next%20into%20its%20constitutional%20compatibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20principle%2C%20when%20applied%20to%20other%20cases%2C%20would%20have%20similarly%20regressive%20consequences%2C%20causing%20a%20permanent%20entrenchment%20of%20the%20status%20quo%20by%20justifying%20it%20using%20lawmakers%E2%80%99%20intellectual%20limitations%20to%20conceptualize%20a%20fairer%2C%20equal%20world%20at%20the%20time%20of%20enactment.%C2%A0In%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1241462%2F%5C%22%3EGitha%20Hariharan%20v.%20RBI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20Court%20could%20have%20noted%20that%20Parliament%2C%20at%20the%20time%20of%20enacting%20the%20Hindu%20Minority%20and%20Guardianship%20Act%2C%201956%2C%20could%20never%20have%20known%20that%20women%20could%20be%20equal%20guardians%20of%20minors%2C%20and%20no%20classification%20between%20%E2%80%9Cmen%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwomen%E2%80%9D%20lay%20in%20the%20subordination%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20to%20guardianship%3B%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1216671%2F%5C%22%3EMadhu%20Kishwar%20v.%20State%20of%20Bihar%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20could%20have%20wholly%20rejected%20tribal%20women%E2%80%99s%20demands%20for%20equal%20succession%20rights%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20%E2%80%93%20when%20undertaking%20the%20codification%20of%20customs%20%E2%80%93%20could%20not%20have%20envisioned%20a%20constitutionally-compliant%2C%20gender-equal%20process%20thereof%3B%20and%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F715470%2F%5C%22%3EVasantha%20R%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20could%20have%20upheld%20Section%2066(1)(b)%20of%20the%20Factories%20Act%2C%201948%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20Parliament%20could%20not%20have%20envisioned%20that%20women%20may%20also%20work%20during%20night%20hours%2C%20making%20their%20exclusion%20an%20unintentional%20incidence%20of%20well-meaning%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20point%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20that%20any%20standard%20enquiring%20into%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20for%20determining%20a%20law%E2%80%99s%20differentia%20is%20bound%20to%20whitewash%20highly%20regressive%2C%20hostile%20acts%20of%20discrimination%20through%20a%20simple%20denial%20of%20the%20classification%E2%80%99s%20existence%2C%20the%20only%20evidence%20for%20which%20a%20Court%20may%20offer%20is%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20epistemic%20limits%2C%20along%20with%20its%20inability%20to%20conceptualize%20an%20equal%20society%20at%20the%20time%20it%20enacted%20the%20relevant%20law.%20Such%20an%20enquiry%2C%20apart%20from%20being%20generally%20historically%20inaccurate%20by%20presuming%20the%20state%20of%20mind%20of%20hundreds%20of%20parliamentarians%20sitting%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20has%20the%20effect%20of%20legitimizing%20present-day%20discrimination%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20past%20parliamentarians%20could%20%3Cem%3Enever%20have%20thought%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20such%20groups%20possessed%20the%20basic%20minimum%20dignity%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Ckept%20in%20mind%E2%80%9D%20while%20being%20excluded!%20In%20other%20words%2C%20such%20groups%20were%20so%20unimportant%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0constituting%2C%20perhaps%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F58730926%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cminuscule%20minority%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0that%20even%20their%20exclusion%20was%20a%20by-product%20of%20things%20running%20their%20natural%20course.%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20reliance%20on%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20IPC%20to%20justify%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20read%20in%20this%20light%2C%20is%20highly%20disturbing%3A%20it%20indicates%20that%20past%20unconstitutionality%20serves%20as%20a%20justification%20for%20present%20discrimination%2C%20for%20such%20unconstitutionality%20was%20the%20%3Cem%3Enorm%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20adhered%20to%20by%20Parliament.%20Further%2C%20in%20case%20this%20logic%20were%20to%20be%20applied%20in%20%3Cem%3ENavtej%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20even%20Section%20377%20would%20have%20likely%20succeeded%20in%20the%20Article%2014%20challenge%2C%20for%20in%201860%2C%20the%20Imperial%20Legislative%20Council%20%E2%80%93%20with%20its%20intellectual%20and%20moral%20limitations%2C%20along%20with%20its%20adherence%20to%20English%20law%20criminalizing%20homosexuality%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0could%20not%20have%20known%20that%20sexual%20intercourse%20in%20non-heterosexual%20relationships%20is%20a%20facet%20of%20human%20dignity%20and%20individual%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20as%20to%20how%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20reliance%20on%20an%20unconstitutional%20provision%20justifies%20its%20choice%20to%20further%20discriminate%2C%20for%20a%20declaration%20of%20unconstitutionality%20has%20effect%20of%20making%20a%20law%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2007%2F415%2F415_2007_2_1501_46897_Judgement_11-Sep-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cvoid%20ab%20initio%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20invalidity%20that%20attaches%20from%20the%20moment%20of%20enactment.%20Section%20377%20was%20invalid%2C%20therefore%2C%20at%20least%20since%20the%20coming%20into%20force%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20in%201950.%20Judicial%20invocation%20of%20parliamentary%20reliance%20on%20invalid%20law%2C%20in%20order%20to%20justify%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20myopic%20imagination%20of%20marriage%20in%20the%20past%2C%20thus%20stands%20in%20murky%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20basis%2C%20I%20submit%20that%20the%20implications%20of%20a%20doctrinal%20adoption%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20to%20determine%20differentia%20are%20highly%20disastrous%2C%20and%20are%20likely%20to%20stultify%20equality%20jurisprudence%20by%20perpetually%20pointing%20to%20a%20regressive%20past.%20The%20only%20way%20such%20stultification%20can%20be%20prevented%2C%20however%2C%20is%20to%20face%20reality%20and%20confront%20factual%2C%20verifiable%20exclusion%2C%20instead%20of%20ruminating%20over%20parliamentarians%E2%80%99%20state%20of%20mind%20in%20the%201950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CClassifying%20without%20classification%E2%80%9D%20and%20no-holds-barred%20objectives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20now%20address%20the%20remaining%20two%20prongs%20of%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20arguments%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Efirst%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20the%20SMA%20actually%20makes%20a%20classification%20involving%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%20%3Cem%3Esecond%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20since%20the%20SMA%20serves%20the%20legitimate%20objective%20of%20providing%20a%20platform%20to%20solemnize%20inter-faith%20marriages%2C%20a%20challenge%20to%20its%20validity%20is%20obviated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20prong%2C%20it%20is%20submitted%20that%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20identification%20of%20the%20classification%20u%2Fs%204%20as%20comprising%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%9D%2C%20instead%20of%20one%20between%20%E2%80%9Cnon-heterosexual%20inter-faith%20couples%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20inter-faith%20couples%E2%80%9D%2C%20constitutes%20a%20complete%20misidentification.%20A%20differentia%2C%20as%20discussed%20above%2C%20must%20comprise%20two%20groups%20%E2%80%93%20one%20included%2C%20and%20another%20excluded.%20In%20stating%20that%20the%20classification%20involves%20only%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%9D%2C%20there%20is%20no%20clarity%20of%20the%20group%20being%20excluded%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20this%20group%E2%80%99s%20inclusion%2C%20apart%20from%20non-heterosexual%20inter-faith%20couples%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0who%20Bhat%2C%20J.%20has%20already%20concluded%2C%20are%20not%20being%20excluded%20by%20the%20SMA.%20One%20argument%20to%20sustain%20his%20identification%20of%20the%20included%20group%2C%20however%2C%20could%20have%20identified%20the%20excluded%20group%20as%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20the%20same%20faith%E2%80%9D.%20This%20identification%2C%20however%2C%20would%20also%20be%20erroneous%2C%20for%20the%20SMA%20does%20not%20prohibit%20a%20couple%2C%20both%20whose%20members%20practise%20the%20same%20faith%2C%20from%20solemnizing%20a%20marriage%20thereunder.%20The%20SMA%2C%20apart%20from%20containing%20no%20same-faith%20prohibition%2C%20specifically%20envisions%20couples%20marrying%20thereunder%20%E2%80%93%20both%20whose%20members%20are%20Hindu%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0u%2Fs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F11410%2F%5C%22%3E21A%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20cannot%2C%20fundamentally%2C%20be%20a%20classification%20involving%20a%20single%20group%20by%20itself%2C%20making%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20identification%20of%20the%20classification%20incorrect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20second%20prong%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20reliance%20on%20the%20objective%20of%20creating%20a%20platform%20for%20solemnizing%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriages%2C%20in%20order%20to%20sustain%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20validity%2C%20whitewashes%20the%20issue%20of%20exclusion.%20To%20recap%2C%20the%20Court%20framed%20the%20question%20as%20to%20whether%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Eoriginal%3C%2Fem%3E%20objective%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20to%20facilitate%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriages%20%E2%80%93%20has%20turned%20illegitimate%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20time.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20Court%20states%20that%20this%20objective%20is%20as%20relevant%20today%20as%20it%20was%20at%20the%20time%20the%20SMA%20was%20enacted%2C%20for%20persons%20seek%20to%20marry%20persons%20of%20different%20faiths%20regularly%20nowadays.%20Bhat%2C%20J.%20also%20remarks%20that%20the%20SMA%20cannot%20be%20deemed%20wholly%20meaningless%20due%20to%20its%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriages%2C%20for%20its%20relevance%20%E2%80%93%20insofar%20as%20it%20concerns%20heterosexual%20marriages%20%E2%80%93%20is%20alive%20and%20well%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6The%20relevance%20of%20SMA%20has%20gained%20more%20ground%2C%20because%20of%20increasing%20awareness%20and%20increasing%20exercise%20of%20choice%20by%20intending%20spouses%20belonging%20to%20different%20faiths%E2%80%A6It%20cannot%20be%20said%2C%20by%20any%20stretch%20of%20the%20imagination%20that%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20from%20the%20fold%20of%20SMA%20has%20resulted%20in%20its%20ceasing%20to%20have%20any%20rationale%2C%20and%20thus%20becoming%20discriminatory%20in%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20however%2C%20was%20uncontested%2C%20for%20none%20argued%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20loss%20of%20legitimacy%20based%20on%20the%20objective%20of%20facilitating%20inter-faith%20marriages%20going%20stale.%20The%20argument%20concerned%20the%20invalidity%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20of%20regulating%20%3Cem%3Eexclusively%3C%2Fem%3E%20heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20which%20caused%20the%20exclusion%20of%20all%20other%20forms.%20An%20assessment%20of%20the%20constitutional%20compatibility%20of%20this%20objective%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20done%20in%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20opinion%2C%20for%20he%20undertakes%20a%20repetitive%20diversion%20to%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20continued%20relevance%20of%20facilitating%20inter-faith%20marriage%2C%20portraying%20the%20latter%20as%20demonstrative%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20commendable%20virtues.%20Such%20virtues%20in%20one%20respect%2C%20however%2C%20are%20no%20justification%20for%20exclusion%20in%20another%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0and%20it%20was%20an%20enquiry%20into%20the%20latter%20that%20was%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20prerogative%20after%20identifying%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20as%20regulating%20exclusively%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriage.%20This%20he%20did%20not%20undertake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaul%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20dissent%20points%20tersely%20to%20such%20errors%3A%20he%20notes%20that%20since%20an%20objective%20must%20be%20constitutionally%20compliant%2C%20an%20objective%20of%20catering%20exclusively%20to%20heterosexual%20couples%20violates%20Article%2015(1)%2C%20and%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20invocation%20thereof%20to%20justify%20the%20classification%20was%2C%20therefore%2C%20wrong.%20Apart%20from%20the%20dissent%2C%20it%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20Bhat%2C%20J.%20sets%20the%20considerations%20of%20inter-faith%20marriage%20and%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%20at%20opposing%20ends%2C%20portraying%20the%20petitioners%20as%20attempting%20to%20undo%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20prized%20progressive%20credentials.%20This%2C%20however%2C%20was%20not%20the%20case%3A%20the%20petitioners%20consistently%20pointed%20to%20the%20necessity%20of%20preserving%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20inter-faith%20marriage%20solemnization%20machinery%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20made%20a%20%E2%80%9Creading%20down%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20SMA%20to%20permit%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%20the%20preferable%20relief%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20declaration%20of%20its%20unconstitutionality%20(%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fwritten-submissions-in-utkarsh-saxena-v-uoi-469115.pdf%5C%22%3EDr.%20Abhishek%20Singhvi%E2%80%99s%20Written%20Submissions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20basis%2C%20I%20submit%20that%20the%20instant%20case%20invokes%20a%20mix%20of%20novel%20constitutional%20doctrine%2C%20erroneous%20class-identification%2C%20and%20deliberate%20diversions%20to%20reject%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20Article%2014%20case.%20The%20most%20dangerous%20development%20of%20the%20judgment%2C%20which%20is%20susceptible%20to%20immense%20misuse%2C%20concerns%20the%20invention%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20standard%2C%20pursuant%20to%20which%20a%20court%20may%20deny%20the%20existence%20of%20factual%2C%20real%20classes%20by%20pointing%20to%20imaginative%20limitations%20to%20envision%20an%20equal%20world%20at%20the%20time%20of%20enactment.%20The%20court%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20states%20that%20non-heterosexual%20persons%20possessed%20no%20dignity%20to%20even%20be%20%3Cem%3Ethought%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20excluded%20from%20marriage%2C%20and%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20not%20the%20subject%20of%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20classification.%20The%20subsequent%20class-misidentification%2C%20along%20with%20portraying%20as%20legitimate%20the%20regulation%20of%20exclusively%20heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20adds%20insult%20to%20injury%2C%20and%20marks%20a%20substantial%20setback%20to%20Indian%20equality%20jurisprudence.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699876847000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fscs-marriage-equality-judgment-manufactured-classifications-and-return-of-minuscule-minorities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court's%20assertion%20that%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%20didn't%20exclude%20non-heterosexual%20marriages%2C%20attributing%20it%20to%20Parliament's%20lack%20of%20awareness%20during%20enactment%2C%20is%20a%20novel%20and%20dangerous%20constitutional%20doctrine%2C%20potentially%20legitimising%20regressive%20laws%20based%20on%20historical%20intellectual%20limitations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fscs-marriage-equality-judgment-manufactured-classifications-and-return-of-minuscule-minorities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Concentration%20of%20fine%2C%20lung-damaging%20particles%20rose%20by%2045%25'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699876832000%