n-ex-nfl-player-among-six-people-killed-in-houston-car-crash-13007230%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Killer%3A%20The%20Clinical%20Assassin%20in%20a%20Film%20Made%20by%20a%20Clinical%20Director%20David%20Fincher%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13161217%2Fimage-1495.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%20in%20David%20Fincher%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20unnamed%20titular%20character%20(Michael%20Fassbender)%20says%20%E2%80%98scepticism%20is%20often%20mistaken%20for%20cynicism%E2%80%99.%20It%E2%80%99s%20something%20that%20could%20be%20said%20for%20the%20director%20too.%20Fincher%2C%20famous%20for%20his%20clinical%20approach%20while%20showing%20human%20beings%20at%20their%20most%20depraved%2C%20has%20often%20been%20described%20as%20a%20cynic.%20He%E2%80%99s%20maintained%20that%20the%20core%20philosophy%20of%20his%20films%20is%3A%20people%20are%20perverts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20one%20delves%20deeper%20into%20his%20work%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20hard%20to%20find%20that%20Fincher%20is%20a%20sceptic%2C%20not%20a%20cynic%2C%20the%20difference%20being%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20automatically%20assume%20the%20worst%20of%20human%20beings.%20He%20probably%20wants%20to%20believe%20in%20goodness%2C%20but%20there%20are%20just%20too%20many%20examples%20in%20the%20world%20to%20plant%20a%20seed%20of%20permanent%20doubt.%20The%20protagonist%20in%20Fincher%E2%80%99s%20latest%20might%20constantly%20remind%20himself%20that%20%E2%80%98empathy%20is%20a%20weakness%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20he%20shows%20himself%20to%20be%20not%20cold-blooded%20on%20more%20than%20one%20occasion%20in%20the%20film.%20Despite%20whatever%20he%20might%20think%20of%20himself%2C%20he%20manages%20to%20find%20his%20moral%20centre%20to%20do%20the%20fair%20thing%2C%20even%20in%20the%20most%20unfair%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plot%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20painfully%20simple%3A%20A%20hitman%20botches%20up%20a%20job%2C%20and%20he%20goes%20on%20the%20run.%20Returning%20home%20to%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%2C%20he%20realises%20his%20employer%20has%20hurt%20his%20long-time%20partner%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20learn%20about%20his%20whereabouts.%20The%20protagonist%2C%20who%20never%20acts%20out%20of%20emotion%20%E2%80%93%20all%20his%20actions%20are%20measured%2C%20he%20blends%20into%20the%20crowd%20like%20sugar%20in%20hot%20milk%20%E2%80%93%20breaks%20his%20rules%20for%20love.%20He%20seeks%20out%20his%20handler%20Hodges%20%5BCharles%20Parnell%5D%2C%20the%20assassins%20sent%20to%20torture%20his%20partner%2C%20and%20the%20client%20%E2%80%93%20a%20billionaire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20plot%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20seems%20direct%2C%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20far-fetched%20to%20think%20that%20the%20film%20could%20present%20itself%20as%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20director%E2%80%99s%20tempestuous%20relationship%20with%20the%20studios%20over%20his%20three-decade%20career.%20Just%20look%20out%20for%20the%20caption%20on%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20poster%3A%20execution%20is%20everything.%20Those%20are%20words%20for%20a%20filmmaker%20to%20die%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFincher%E2%80%99s%20run-ins%20with%20the%20Hollywood%20system%20have%20been%20the%20stuff%20of%20legends%2C%20especially%20the%20way%20he%20began%20his%20career%20with%20the%20troubled%20production%20of%20%3Cem%3EAlien%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1992).%20After%20his%20adaptation%20of%20Steig%20Larsson%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EMillennium%3C%2Fem%3E%20trilogy%20was%20shut%20down%20following%20just%20one%20film%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Girl%20with%20The%20Dragon%20Tattoo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%2C%20and%20the%20show%20%3Cem%3EMindhunter%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2017-2019)%20was%20discontinued%20after%20two%20seasons%20for%20being%20%E2%80%98too%20expensive%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20numbers%20it%20ended%20up%20drawing%2C%20one%20can%20almost%20sense%20the%20weariness%20in%20the%2061-year-old%20filmmaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20previous%20film%2C%20%3Cem%3EMank%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2021)%2C%20a%20black-and-white%2C%20no-questions-asked%20passion%20project%2C%20based%20on%20a%20screenplay%20written%20by%20his%20father%20(Jack%20Fincher)%20on%20the%20making%20of%20%3Cem%3ECitizen%20Kane%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1931)%2C%20felt%20like%20one%20of%20his%20more%20personal%20films.%20And%20now%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eit%20feels%20like%20Fincher%20is%20looking%20inwards%20more%20than%20outwards%20for%20inspiration.%20Even%20his%20choice%20of%20actor%2C%20Michael%20Fassbender%2C%20who%20was%20brought%20out%20of%20hibernation%20after%20being%20chewed%20out%20in%20six%20consecutive%20studio%20flops%2C%20seems%20to%20be%20telling%20its%20own%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdapted%20from%20a%20French%20graphic%20novel%20of%20the%20same%20name%20by%20Alexis%20%E2%80%98Matz%E2%80%99%20Nolent%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20opens%20with%20the%20protagonist%20talking%20about%20how%20contract%20killing%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20job%20worth%20pursuing%20if%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20endure%20the%20waiting.%20He%20could%20be%20talking%20about%20filmmaking%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20a%20vocation%20about%20which%20actor%20John%20Candy%20once%20remarked%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20get%20paid%20for%20waiting%2C%20I%20throw%20in%20the%20acting%20for%20free!%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20Fincher%20at%20his%20most%20indulgent%20%E2%80%93%20sharing%20his%20philosophies%20with%20the%20world%20through%20a%20protagonist%20who%20is%20as%20dry%2C%20disciplined%2C%20meticulous%20and%20proud%20as%20a%20craftsman%20as%20the%20filmmaker%20is.%20Over%20the%20normal%20course%20of%20events%2C%20the%20protagonist%20dispassionately%20looks%20at%20life%20as%20something%20to%20endure.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20self-centered%20way%20of%20living%20saying%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20give%20a%20damn%E2%80%9D%20about%20anything%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20help%20him%20in%20his%20work.%20That%E2%80%99s%20until%20someone%20hurts%20a%20loved%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFincher%20takes%20the%20template%20of%20hitman%20films%20like%20%3Cem%3EJason%20Bourne%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3EJohn%20Wick%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20slowly%20draining%20all%20the%20sexiness%20out%20of%20it.%20It%20seems%20a%20very%20deliberate%20choice%2C%20where%20he%20takes%20the%20very%20template%20of%20a%20genre%20he%20has%20helped%20establish%2C%20and%20turns%20it%20inside%20out.%20Fassbender%20%E2%80%93%20who%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20starred%20in%20movies%20in%20three%20years%20%E2%80%93%20seems%20to%20be%20enjoying%20his%20director%E2%80%99s%20quiet%20rebellion%20against%20what%20is%20expected%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98cool%E2%80%99%20Fincher%20film.%20He%E2%80%99s%20dressed%20and%20styled%20unmemorably%20throughout%2C%20in%20Khakis%2C%20tracksuits%2C%20baseball%20caps.%20Even%20though%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20usual%20globetrotting%20in%20a%20film%20like%20this%2C%20where%20the%20killer%20hops%20on%20transcontinental%20flights%20like%20they%20were%20local%20trains%20in%20Bombay%2C%20Fincher%20never%20milks%20the%20changing%20geography%20with%20the%20cliched%20top-shot%20of%20a%20city%2C%20with%20the%20name%20appearing%20as%20a%20title%20card%20on%20screen.%20Instead%2C%20he%20makes%20mundane%20observations%20about%20them%20like%20any%20world-weary%20traveller%3A%20%E2%80%9CParis%20is%20a%20city%20that%20wakes%20up%20slowly%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CNew%20Orleans%2C%20a%20thousand%20restaurants%E2%80%A6%20one%20menu.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20one%20fist%20fight%20sequence%20in%20the%20entire%20film%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%20seems%20to%20be%20designed%20in%20a%20way%20to%20look%20functional%2C%20not%20stylish.%20However%2C%20Fincher%E2%80%99s%20precision%20shows%20up%20in%20the%20closing%20moments%20of%20the%20scene%2C%20when%20the%20killer%20needs%20to%20escape%20a%20pitbull.%20The%20timing%20and%20choreography%20of%20this%20last%20bit%20is%20unsurprisingly%20exquisite.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20scene%20fe