%20had%20been%20foreign%20secretary%2C%20before%20announcing%20Cameron%20as%20Cleverly's%20surprise%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECameron%2C%2057%2C%20quit%20as%20prime%20minister%20in%202016%20after%20losing%20the%20Brexit%20referendum.%20He%20stood%20down%20as%20an%20MP%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20became%20mired%20in%20scandal%20in%202021%2C%20after%20lobbying%20the%20UK%20government%20for%20finance%20group%20Greensill%20Capital%2C%20which%20later%20collapsed%20and%20the%20episode%20was%20seen%20as%20badly%20tarnishing%20his%20reputation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECameron%20will%20be%20made%20a%20life%20peer%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%2C%20Britain's%20upper%20chamber%20of%20parliament%2C%20Downing%20Street%20announced%2C%20meaning%20that%20he%20can%20sit%20in%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20leader%20said%20he%20%26quot%3Bgladly%20accepted%26quot%3B%20the%20role%20as%20Britain%20faced%20%26quot%3Ba%20daunting%20set%20of%20international%20challenges%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20I%20have%20been%20out%20of%20front-line%20politics%20for%20the%20last%20seven%20years%2C%20I%20hope%20that%20my%20experience%20--%20as%20Conservative%20leader%20for%2011%20years%20and%20prime%20minister%20for%20six%20--%20will%20assist%20me%20in%20helping%20the%20prime%20minister%20to%20meet%20these%20vital%20challenges%2C%26quot%3B%20Cameron%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Desperate'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20her%20dismissal%2C%20Braverman%20said%20%26quot%3Bit%20has%20been%20the%20greatest%20privilege%20of%20my%20life%20to%20serve%20as%20home%20secretary%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20have%20more%20to%20say%20in%20due%20course%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20are%20part%20of%20Sunak's%20first%20major%20reshuffle%20of%20his%20top%20ministers%20since%20becoming%20the%20country's%20leader%20in%20October%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Conservatives%2C%20in%20power%20for%20nearly%2014%20years%2C%20said%20the%20changes%20%26quot%3Bstrengthen%20his%20team%20in%20government%20to%20deliver%20long-term%20decisions%20for%20a%20brighter%20future%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESet%20to%20be%20announced%20throughout%20the%20day%2C%20they%20are%20also%20expected%20to%20reward%20loyalists%20and%20younger%20emerging%20MPs%2C%20as%20the%20party%20struggles%20for%20popularity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECameron's%20unexpected%20return%20surprised%20even%20those%20who%20comment%20daily%20on%20British%20politics%2C%20and%20was%20viewed%20as%20having%20been%20made%20with%20the%20next%20general%20election%20firmly%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tories%20have%20trailed%20the%20main%20Labour%20opposition%20by%20double-digit%20margins%20throughout%20Sunak's%20time%20in%20power%2C%20and%20are%20widely%20tipped%20to%20lose%20the%20contest%20due%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20he%20has%20a%20high%20profile%20and%20contacts%20around%20the%20world%2C%20Cameron's%20appointment%20may%20not%20prove%20a%20vote%20winner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolling%20in%20September%20showed%2045%20percent%20of%20UK%20adults%20felt%20unfavourably%20towards%20him%2C%20while%20only%20around%20a%20quarter%20held%20a%20favourable%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETim%20Bale%2C%20politics%20professor%20at%20London's%20Queen%20Mary%20University%2C%20said%20Sunak%20was%20likely%20drawn%20to%20Cameron's%20%26quot%3Bclout%20on%20the%20international%20stage%26quot%3B%20and%20hoped%20to%20appeal%20to%20increasingly%20dissatisfied%20centrist%20and%20centre-right%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20sceptical%20that%20it'll%20make%20much%20difference%20on%20that%20or%20any%20other%20score%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20noted.%20%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20desperate%20--%20because%20that%20is%20what%20it%20is!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Tofu-eating%20wokerati'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBraverman%20had%20stoked%20controversy%20throughout%20her%20tenure%2C%20taking%20a%20hardline%20stance%20on%20immigration%20in%20particular%20and%20regularly%20wading%20into%20so-called%20culture%20wars%20issues%20which%20are%20seen%20as%20dividing%20the%20electorate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20her%20position%20became%20increasingly%20untenable%20after%20she%20last%20week%20wrote%20an%20explosive%20newspaper%20article%2C%20without%20Sunak's%20approval%2C%20accusing%20police%20of%20bias%20towards%20left-wing%20causes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20was%20blamed%20for%20stoking%20tensions%20ahead%20of%20a%20weekend%20of%20protests%20calling%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%2C%20which%20coincided%20with%20Armistice%20Day%20events%2C%20and%20prompted%20calls%20for%20her%20to%20be%20sacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20said%20her%20comments%20had%20encouraged%20far-right%20protesters%20to%20hold%20counter%20demos%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20main%20march%20on%20Saturday%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20dozens%20of%20arrests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDowning%20Street%20launched%20an%20investigation%20into%20how%20the%20article%20was%20published%20without%20its%20consent%2C%20as%20required%20by%20the%20ministerial%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBraverman's%20comments%2C%20seen%20as%20red%20meat%20to%20the%20right%20wing%20of%20the%20governing%20Conservative%20party%2C%20were%20also%20viewed%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20position%20herself%20as%20a%20future%20leader%20of%20the%20Tories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20came%20after%20she%20described%20the%20rallies%20calling%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20as%20%26quot%3Bhate%20marches%26quot%3B%2C%20days%20after%20claiming%20some%20people%20were%20homeless%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Blifestyle%20choice%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20right-winger%20has%20attacked%20her%20critics%20as%20liberal%20%26quot%3Btofu-eating%20wokerati%26quot%3B%20while%20saying%20shortly%20after%20she%20was%20appointed%20that%20sending%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20Rwanda%20was%20her%20%26quot%3Bdream%26q