ublished%22%3A1699871609000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F5E1A%2Fproduction%2F_131709042_tv089499036.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67402000%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Seismic%20activity%20has%20been%20less%20intense%20but%20a%20volcanic%20eruption%20still%20seems%20imminent%2C%20scientists%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A66%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67402000%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67402000.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67402000.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Insider%20the%20strange%2C%20secretive%20rise%20of%20the%20'overemployed'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20remote%20worker%20on%20two%20desktops%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d5e9a3cc84b4dfaffcd89%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERemote%20workers%20are%20%26quot%3Bdouble%20dipping%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20taking%20two%20or%20more%20full-time%20jobs%20at%20the%20same%20time%20%E2%80%94%20without%20their%20bosses%20knowing.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Bryan%20Roque%20lost%20his%20job%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Amazon.%20Part%20of%20him%20was%20relieved.%20He'd%20been%20working%20himself%20to%20the%20bone%20for%20months%20on%20end%2C%20and%20he%20felt%20completely%20burned%20out.%20But%20the%20timing%20was%20tough%3A%20The%20company%20was%20dumping%20him%20into%20the%20worst%20job%20market%20since%20the%20Great%20Depression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoque%20called%20his%20parents%20to%20give%20them%20the%20bad%20news%2C%20then%20packed%20up%20his%20apartment%20and%20moved%20back%20in%20with%20them.%20He%20eventually%20found%20a%20new%20job%2C%20a%20position%20at%20IBM%20that%20was%20fully%20remote%2C%20but%20an%20underlying%20anxiety%20stayed%20with%20him.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20no%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20like%20that%20I%20was%20under%20the%20whims%20of%20a%20company%20that%20gets%20to%20decide%20whether%20I'm%20employed%20or%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20less%20than%20a%20year%20into%20the%20job%20at%20IBM%2C%20when%20a%20recruiter%20from%20Meta%20came%20calling%2C%20Roque%20had%20a%20thought.%20The%20normal%20thing%20would%20be%20to%20quit%20his%20old%20job%20and%20accept%20the%20new%20position%2C%20which%20was%20also%20fully%20remote.%20But%20what%20if%20he%20kept%20his%20old%20job%2C%20and%20secretly%20took%20on%20the%20new%20one%2C%20too%3F%20All%20he%20had%20to%20do%20was%20two-time%20IBM%2C%20and%20he%20could%20double%20his%20income%20as%20well%20as%20his%20job%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20mulled%20the%20idea%2C%20he%20discovered%20that%20he%20wasn't%20alone.%20There's%20a%20whole%20community%20of%20professionals%20online%20who%20trade%20tips%20about%20juggling%20jobs%20on%20the%20sly.%20They%20describe%20themselves%20as%20%26quot%3Boveremployed%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20remarkably%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20be%20getting%20away%20with%20it.%20Helping%20them%20evade%20detection%20is%20a%20guy%20who%20goes%20by%20the%20pseudonym%20Isaac%2C%20who%20started%20the%20blog%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foveremployed.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOveremployed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20to%20share%20his%20secrets%20as%20the%20OG%20overemployed%20worker.%20Today%20there%20are%20some%20300%2C000%20members%20of%20the%20community%20on%20Discord%20and%20Reddit%20who%20celebrate%20one%20another's%20successes%2C%20commiserate%20on%20their%20failures%2C%20and%20swap%20secrets%20for%20fooling%20their%20bosses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20Roque%20set%20out%20to%20join%20them.%20He%20clinched%20an%20offer%20from%20Meta%2C%20landed%20another%20from%20Tinder%2C%20and%20after%20negotiating%20the%20two%20against%20each%20other%20for%20more%20pay%2C%20he%20accepted%20both%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20in%20addition%20to%20keeping%20his%20gig%20at%20IBM.%20Fifteen%20months%20earlier%2C%20he'd%20been%20unemployed.%20Now%20he%20was%20suddenly%20employed%20three%20times%20over%20%E2%80%94%20and%20on%20track%20to%20earn%20a%20combined%20salary%20of%20more%20than%20%24820%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHolding%20down%20multiple%20jobs%20has%20long%20been%20a%20backbreaking%20way%20for%20low-wage%20workers%20to%20get%20by.%20But%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20phenomenon%20has%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20among%20professionals%20like%20Roque%2C%20who%20have%20seized%20on%20the%20privacy%20provided%20by%20remote%20work%20to%20secretly%20take%20on%20two%20or%20more%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20multiplying%20their%20paychecks%20without%20working%20much%20more%20than%20a%20standard%2040-hour%20workweek.%20The%20move%20is%20not%20only%20culturally%20taboo%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20a%20fireable%20offense%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20could%20expose%20the%20cheaters%20to%20a%20lawsuit%20if%20they're%20caught.%20To%20learn%20their%20methods%20and%20motivations%2C%20I%20spent%20several%20weeks%20hanging%20out%20among%20the%20overemployed%20online.%20What%2C%20I%20wondered%2C%20does%20this%20group%20of%20W-2%20renegades%20have%20to%20tell%20us%20about%20the%20nature%20of%20work%20%E2%80%94%20and%20of%20loyalty%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20age%20of%20remote%20employment%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20immersing%20yourself%20in%20the%20overemployed%20forums%2C%20it%20helps%20to%20know%20some%20of%20the%20lingo.%20Those%20who%20consider%20themselves%20OE%20rank%20each%20of%20their%20jobs%20by%20the%20priority%20they%20place%20on%20it.%20J1%20is%20the%20favorite%2C%20the%20one%20they'll%20tend%20to%20before%20the%20others.%20J2%20is%20the%20backup%2C%20J3%20is%20the%20backup%20of%20the%20backup%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20The%20trick%20is%20to%20maximize%20your%20TC%20(total%20compensation)%20while%20minimizing%20your%20HPW%20(hours%20worked%20per%20week%20on%20each%20job).%20If%20you%20see%20inexplicable%20references%20to%20gaming%20(e.g.%2C%20%26quot%3BShould%20I%20take%20on%20a%203rd%20Minecraft%20server%3F%26quot%3B)%20that's%20just%20code%20for%20an%20OE%20job.%20They%20know%20that%20outsiders%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20even%20their%20bosses%20%E2%80%94%20are%20lurking%20on%20the%20forums%2C%20so%20they%20try%20to%20create%20the%20impression%20they're%20talking%20about%20something%20innocent%2C%20the%20way%20a%20mobster%20might%20talk%20about%20accepting%20a%20%26quot%3Bcontract%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bdo%20a%20piece%20of%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20commitment%20to%20secrecy%20is%20the%20first%20pillar%20of%20the%20OE%20ethos.%20They%20freeze%20their%20employment%20histories%20with%20Equifax%20and%20hibernate%20their%20LinkedIn%20profiles%2C%20so%20employers%20can't%20see%20they're%20holding%20multiple%20jobs.%20They%20tell%20no%20one%20what%20they're%20up%20to%2C%20barring%20their%20spouse%20and%20maybe%20their%20accountant%20%E2%80%94%20hence%20their%20many%20references%20to%20%26quot%3BFight%20Club.%26quot%3B%20When%20a%20coworker%20sends%20them%20some%20article%20about%20OE%2C%20they%20feign%20surprise.%20%3Cem%3EThere's%20no%20way%20I%20could%20handle%20two%20jobs%20when%20I'm%20so%20busy%20with%20just%20one!%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20first%20rule%20of%20OE%20is%20you%20do%20not%20talk%20about%20OE.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223093%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Remote%20worker%20with%20a%20shadow%20representing%20secrecy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d5f10b788914e5553ac37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20first%20rule%20of%20OE%20is%20you%20do%20not%20talk%20about%20OE.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20OE%20hustlers%20have%20some%20tried-and-true%20hacks.%20Taking%20on%20a%20second%20or%20third%20full-time%20job%3F%20Given%20how%20time-consuming%20the%20onboarding%20process%20can%20be%2C%20you%20should%20take%20a%20week%20or%20two%20of%20vacation%20from%20your%20other%20jobs.%20It%20helps%20if%20you%20can%20stagger%20your%20jobs%20by%20time%20zone%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20one%20that%20operates%20during%20New%20York%20hours%2C%20say%2C%20and%20another%20on%20California%20time.%20Keep%20separate%20work%20calendars%20for%20each%20job%20%E2%80%94%20but%20to%20avoid%20double-bookings%2C%20be%20sure%20to%20block%20off%20%3Cem%3Eall%20%3C%2Fem%3Eyour%20calendars%20as%20soon%20as%20a%20new%20meeting%20gets%20scheduled.%20And%20don't%20skimp%20on%20the%20tech%20that%20will%20make%20your%20life%20a%20bit%20easier.%20Mouse%20jigglers%20create%20the%20appearance%20that%20you're%20online%20when%20you're%20busy%20tending%20to%20your%20other%20jobs.%20A%20KVM%20switch%20helps%20you%20control%20multiple%20laptops%20from%20the%20same%20keyboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20OE%20hustlers%20brag%20about%20shirking%20their%20responsibilities.%20For%20them%2C%20being%20overemployed%20is%20all%20about%20putting%20one%20over%20on%20their%20employers.%20But%20most%20in%20the%20community%20take%20pride%20in%20doing%20their%20jobs%2C%20and%20doing%20them%20well.%20That%2C%20after%20all%2C%20is%20the%20single%20best%20way%20to%20avoid%20detection%3A%20Don't%20give%20your%20bosses%20%E2%80%94%20any%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20a%20reason%20to%20become%20suspicious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20reason%20people%20get%20caught%20is%20because%20they're%20slacking%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20George%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%20who's%20held%20as%20many%20as%20four%20jobs%20at%20a%20time.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20been%20caught.%20I%20actually%20do%20the%20work.%26quot%3B%20(All%20the%20OEers%20I%20interviewed%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20Bryan%20Roque%2C%20agreed%20to%20speak%20only%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eon%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity.)%20Does%20working%20multiple%20full-time%20jobs%20require%20burning%20the%20midnight%20oil%3F%20Sure%2C%20once%20in%20a%20while%2C%20when%20the%20shit%20hits%20the%20fan%20at%20all%20your%20companies%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20But%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20people%20average%20no%20more%20than%2050%20hours%20of%20work%20a%20week%2C%20and%20usually%20closer%20to%2040.%20So%20what's%20their%20secret%20to%20condensing%20their%20workloads%20to%20what%20should%20be%20an%2080-%2C%20or%20120-%2C%20or%20160-hour%20workweek%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMostly%2C%20they're%20just%20really%2C%20really%20good%20at%20their%20jobs%2C%20which%20enables%20them%20to%20work%20fast.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20at%20the%20top%20of%20my%20game%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Allison%2C%20a%20woman%20with%2016%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20her%20field%20who%20took%20on%20two%20full-time%20roles.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20I%20was%20applying%20for%20the%20second%20job%2C%20I%20made%20sure%20it%20was%20well%20within%20what%20I%20know%20to%20be%20my%20skillset.%26quot%3B%20One%20OE%20strategy%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20is%20to%20intentionally%20seek%20out%20roles%20that%20are%20too%20junior%20for%20you.%20That%20ensures%20the%20assignments%20you%20get%20will%20be%20pretty%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20with%20multiple%20jobs%20also%20seek%20out%20positions%20they%20hope%20will%20be%20OE-friendly%20%E2%80%94%20light%20on%20meetings%2C%20as%20well%20as%20on%20the%20workload.%20The%20process%20requires%20a%20lot%20of%20trial%20and%20error%2C%20like%20trading%20cards%20until%20you%20get%20the%20perfect%20hand.%20Cole%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%2C%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20J2%20because%20his%20J1%20required%20so%20little%20work%20%E2%80%94%20often%20as%20little%20as%20two%20or%20three%20hours%20a%20week.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20extra%20time%20on%20my%20hands%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20I%20figured%20I%20could%20use%20that%20time%20more%20productively%20than%20just%20watching%20videos%20on%20YouTube.%26quot%3B%20But%20he's%20been%20forced%20to%20cycle%20through%20several%20J2s%2C%20looking%20for%20a%20role%20that%20matches%20his%20J1.%20%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20found%20the%20same%20work-life%20balance%20and%20compensation%20at%20another%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consequences%20for%20getting%20caught%20actually%20appear%20to%20be%20fairly%20low.%20Matthew%20Berman%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20who%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20unofficial%20go-to%20lawyer%20in%20the%20OE%20community%2C%20hasn't%20encountered%20anyone%20who%20has%20been%20hit%20with%20a%20lawsuit%20for%20holding%20a%20second%20job.%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20time%2C%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20worth%20suing%20an%20employee%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20But%20many%20say%20the%20stress%20of%20the%20OE%20life%20can%20get%20to%20you.%20George%2C%20the%20software%20engineer%2C%20has%20trouble%20sleeping%20at%20night%20because%20of%20his%20fear%20of%20getting%20caught.%20Others%20acknowledge%20that%20the%20rigors%20of%20juggling%20multiple%20jobs%20have%20hurt%20their%20marriages.%20One%20channel%20on%20the%20OE%20Discord%20is%20dedicated%20to%20discussions%20of%20family%20life%2C%20mostly%20among%20dads%20with%20young%20kids.%20People%20in%20the%20channel%20sometimes%20ask%20for%20relationship%20advice%2C%20and%20the%20responses%20they%20get%20from%20the%20other%20dads%20are%20sweet.%20%26quot%3BYour%20regard%20for%20your%20partner%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20advised%20of%20marriage%2C%20%26quot%3Bshould%20outweigh%20your%20desire%20for%20validation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20concern%20that's%20dominating%20the%20OE%20forums%20these%20days%20is%20the%20return-to-office%20push%20underway%20at%20many%20companies.%20What%20do%20you%20do%20if%20one%20of%20your%20employers%20requires%20you%20to%20start%20showing%20up%20in%20person%3F%20That's%20what%20happened%20to%20Roque%2C%20the%20IBM-Meta-Tinder%20engineer%2C%20when%20Meta%20asked%20him%20to%20come%20into%20the%20office%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20a%20week.%20Sometimes%20he%20wasn't%20able%20to%20book%20a%20conference%20room%20to%20take%20his%20Tinder%20and%20IBM%20calls%20in%20privacy%2C%20leading%20to%20some%20nerve-racking%20conversations%20out%20in%20Meta's%20open-plan%20office%2C%20where%20anyone%20might%20overhear%20him.%20One%20time%20he%20accidentally%20connected%20his%20Tinder%20laptop%20to%20Meta's%20WiFi%20network%2C%20rather%20than%20using%20his%20phone's%20hot%20spot%2C%20and%20Tinder%20immediately%20noticed.%20It%20was%20a%20close%20call%3A%20When%20Tinder%20asked%20why%20he%20was%20remoting%20in%20from%20Meta%2C%20he%20quickly%20improvised%20a%20story%20about%20how%20he%20was%20working%20at%20a%20friend's%20office.%20%26quot%3BThey%20basically%20told%20me%2C%20'Oh%2C%20just%20so%20you%20know%2C%20we%20recommend%20you%20don't%20do%20that%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'Makes%20sense.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EJob%20jugglers%20in%20the%20OE%20forums%20often%20post%20about%20how%20much%20money%20they're%20making.%20One%20person%20claimed%20to%20be%20earning%20%242%20million%20from%20nine%20jobs%3B%20a%20few%20others%20posted%20about%20making%20%241%20million.%20But%20those%20whose%20earnings%20I%20was%20able%20to%20verify%20are%20earning%20less%20than%20that.%20Isaac%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20Overemployed%20blog%2C%20makes%20about%20%24600%2C000%20from%20his%20two%20tech%20jobs.%20Cole%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%2C%20makes%20about%20%24500%2C000.%20At%20her%20peak%2C%20Allison%20was%20making%20%24260%2C000%20from%20her%20jobs%20as%20a%20business%20analyst%20and%20a%20product%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Remote%20worker%20putting%20coin%20in%20piggy%20bank%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d5f3b3cc84b4dfaffcdba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221660%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20the%20first%20pillar%20of%20OE%20is%20secrecy%2C%20the%20second%20is%20frugality.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20job%20jugglers%20don't%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebrag%20about%2C%20oddly%2C%20is%20how%20they%20spend%20their%20money.%20I%20kept%20looking%20for%20flashy%20anecdotes%20about%20fast%20cars%20and%20luxury%20vacations%2C%20but%20all%20anyone%20seemed%20to%20talk%20about%20was%20saving%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20saving%20some%20more.%20If%20the%20first%20pillar%20of%20OE%20is%20secrecy%2C%20the%20second%20is%20frugality.%20Many%20in%20the%20community%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20adherents%20of%20the%20movement%20known%20as%20FIRE%2C%20short%20for%20Financial%20Independence%2C%20Retire%20Early.%20George%2C%20who%20is%20in%20his%2020s%2C%20told%20me%20he's%20on%20track%20to%20retire%20by%20the%20time%20he's%2035.%20The%20overemployed%20prioritize%20paying%20down%20their%20credit-card%20debt%2C%20student%20loans%2C%20and%20mortgages.%20The%20one%20splurge%20I%20saw%20someone%20proudly%20volunteer%20was%20tickets%20to%20a%20Taylor%20Swift%20concert%20for%20their%20daughter.%20When%20newbies%20post%20their%20success%20stories%2C%20veterans%20chime%20in%20with%20sober%20warnings%20about%20what%20they%20call%20%3Cem%3Elifestyle%20creep%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%26quot%3BOE%20is%20about%20financial%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20recently%20advised.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20inflate%20your%20lifestyle%2C%20you%20lose%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20another%20incentive%3A%20Unlike%20most%20Americans%2C%20those%20who%20work%20multiple%20jobs%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20layoffs.%20For%20Roque%2C%20that%20relief%20outweighed%20the%20stress%20of%20his%20added%20workload%20and%20the%20vigilance%20required%20to%20keep%20his%20three%20jobs%20a%20secret.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20being%20super-dependent%20on%20one%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20control%20over%20whether%20I%20had%20an%20income%20or%20not.%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20he%20ultimately%20wound%20up%20replacing%20his%20jobs%20at%20IBM%20and%20Meta%20and%20Tinder%20with%20a%20single%20new%20one%2C%20to%20give%20himself%20time%20to%20enjoy%20other%20pursuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20know%20%E2%80%94%20what%20interested%20me%20the%20most%20%E2%80%94%20is%20whether%20those%20who%20are%20overemployed%20feel%20guilty%20about%20what%20they're%20doing.%20There's%20no%20way%20around%20the%20fact%20that%20they're%20breaking%20the%20rules%3A%20In%20exchange%20for%20a%20salary%2C%20they%20promised%20not%20to%20work%20for%20anyone%20else.%20Did%20they%20feel%20bad%20about%20breaking%20that%20promise%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20forums%20include%20quite%20a%20few%20posts%20in%20the%20screw-the-man%20tenor%20you%20see%20all%20over%20Reddit%20%E2%80%94%20one%20person%20boasted%20about%20being%20a%20%26quot%3Bmonetary%20mercenary.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20overemployed%20I%20spoke%20with%20came%20across%20like%20decent%20people.%20They%20genuinely%20seem%20to%20care%20about%20fulfilling%20their%20obligations%20to%20the%20people%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20certain%20moral%20ick%20to%20taking%20two%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20George%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20some%20really%20nice%20bosses%2C%20so%20the%20way%20I%20compensate%20is%20by%20going%20the%20extra%20mile.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%20says%20she%20worried%2C%20at%20first%2C%20that%20she%20was%20taking%20a%20job%20that%20could%20have%20gone%20to%20someone%20who%20didn't%20have%20one.%20With%20unemployment%20at%203.9%25%2C%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20jobs%20to%20go%20around%20right%20now%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20a%20legitimate%20concern%2C%20especially%20given%20all%20the%20recent%20layoffs%20in%20the%20tech%20industry.%20Allison%20ultimately%20justified%20taking%20a%20second%20job%20because%20her%20husband%20wasn't%20working%20so%20he%20could%20care%20for%20older%20family%20members.%20As%20a%20couple%2C%20she%20reasons%2C%20they%20still%20have%20the%20same%20number%20of%20jobs%20as%20a%20normal%20dual-income%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20say%20they%20don't%20feel%20bad%20for%20a%20simpler%20reason%3A%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebecause%20they%20do%20the%20work%20that's%20required%20of%20them.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20happy%20with%20what%20I'm%20producing%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Cole%2C%20who's%20been%20promoted%20twice%20at%20his%20J1%20since%20he%20started%20taking%20on%20second%20jobs.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20feel%20bad%20about%20what%20I'm%20doing%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20bosses%2C%20of%20course%2C%20would%20argue%20that%20they're%20paying%20these%20employees%20to%20work%20full-time.%20If%20you%20get%20your%20work%20done%20quickly%2C%20the%20traditional%20expectation%20is%20you%20should%20let%20your%20supervisor%20know%20you're%20available%20to%20take%20on%20more%20tasks.%20You%20owe%20it%20to%20your%20company%20to%20put%20in%20the%20hours%20you're%20being%20paid%20for%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20precisely%20what%20many%20of%20the%20overemployed%20say%20they%20used%20to%20do%2C%20back%20in%20their%20days%20as%20career%20monogamists.%20And%20what%20did%20that%20get%20them%3F%20A%20lousy%20raise%20that%20got%20wiped%20out%20by%20inflation.%20Unmet%20promises%20of%20a%20promotion.%20Layoffs%20at%20the%20first%20sign%20of%20turmoil%2C%20delivered%20by%20a%20single%20email%20that%20shuts%20you%20out%20of%20the%20company's%20system%20with%20no%20warning.%20Loyalty%2C%20they%20decided%2C%20doesn't%20pay.%20If%20you%20can't%20trust%20one%20employer%20to%20do%20right%20by%20you%2C%20better%20to%20have%20two%20or%20three%20of%20them%20as%20backups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20core%2C%20overemployment%20represents%20a%20new%20social%20contract%20being%20forged%20in%20an%20era%20that%20has%20left%20the%20old%2C%20unspoken%20agreement%20around%20work%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bstick%20with%20us%20for%20life%20and%20we'll%20treat%20you%20like%20family%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20in%20tatters.%20Professionals%20in%20the%20OE%20forums%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20way%20that%20will%20more%20reliably%20reward%20them%20for%20their%20talents%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it%20requires%20an%20ungodly%20degree%20of%20risk%20tolerance%20and%20a%20champion-level%20poker%20face.%20%26quot%3BMy%20parents%20told%20me%2C%20'Don't%20switch%20companies%2C%20grow%20in%20one%20company%2C%20be%20loyal%20to%20one%20company%2C%20and%20they'll%20be%20loyal%20to%20you%2C'%26quot%3B%20George%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20may%20have%20been%20true%20in%20their%20days%2C%20but%20it%20definitely%20isn't%20today%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20is%2C%20employers%20themselves%20have%20started%20moving%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20hiring%20people%20who%20have%20multiple%20jobs.%20Since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20many%20companies%20have%20been%20bringing%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-employers-quiet-quitting-contractors-part-time-gig-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20independent%20contractors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20are%20often%20paid%20by%20the%20project%2C%20not%20by%20the%20hour.%20Critically%2C%20these%20gigs%20come%20with%20no%20expectation%20of%20loyalty.%20As%20I%20reported%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20that's%20terrifying%20for%20us%20normies%2C%20who%20depend%20on%20our%20employer%20to%20provide%20us%20with%20health%20insurance%20and%20other%20benefits.%20But%20it's%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20the%20overemployed.%20Many%20in%20the%20OE%20community%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20fact%2C%20have%20taken%20advantage%20of%20the%20trend%20by%20getting%20a%20full-time%20J1%20that%20provides%20them%20with%20health%20insurance%20and%20then%20taking%20J2s%20and%20J3s%20that%20are%20contractor%20positions%2C%20which%20often%20come%20with%20higher%20pay%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic-era%20rise%20of%20remote%20and%20hybrid%20work%20has%20also%20introduced%20employers%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-performance-evaluations-management-reviews-promotions-raises%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20way%20of%20measuring%20productivity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%20of%20tracking%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20that%20employees%20log%20at%20their%20desks%2C%20many%20supervisors%20are%20now%20evaluating%20employees%20based%20on%20the%20actual%20work%20they%20produce.%20Given%20this%20more%20flexible%2C%20results-oriented%20approach%20to%20management%2C%20some%20bosses%20may%20get%20to%20the%20point%20where%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdouble-dipping-work-multiple-remote-jobs-is-okay-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20an%20employee's%20second%20job%2C%20as%20long%20as%20the%20work%20they're%20getting%20from%20the%20employee%20is%20first-rate.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20'exceeds'%20on%20my%20reviews%20for%20both%20jobs%20last%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Allison%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20feel%20guilty%20when%20you're%20doing%20what%20you're%20supposed%20to%20be%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20a%20strong%20argument%20to%20be%20made%20that%20the%20overemployed%20could%20actually%20wind%20up%20fueling%20a%20backlash%20from%20bosses.%20Many%20CEOs%20have%20already%20grown%20suspicious%20of%20remote%20work%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailybeast.com%2Fclearlink-ceo-james-clarke-delivers-unhinged-speech-as-he-blasts-his-staff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econvinced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20work-from-home%20employees%20are%20taking%20advantage%20of%20them%2C%20and%20reports%20of%20two-timing%20scofflaws%20only%20serve%20to%20confirm%20those%20fears.%20From%20a%20traditional%20management%20perspective%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20experienced%20employees%20can%20finish%20their%20job%20in%20far%20less%20than%2040%20hours%20a%20week%20argues%20for%20either%20(1)%20giving%20full-time%20staffers%20more%20work%20or%20(2)%20replacing%20them%20with%20independent%20contractors.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20who%20do%20this%20stuff%20really%20just%20make%20it%20worse%20for%20everyone%20else%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Redditor%20wrote%20in%20a%20much-villified%20post%20on%20the%20subreddit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Foveremployed%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%2Foveremployed%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BNot%20here%20to%20hate.%20Just%20want%20you%20guys%20to%20rethink%20what%20you're%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222067%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20desktop%20computer%20showing%20three%20trophies%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d5f623cc84b4dfaffcdce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221928%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20'exceeds'%20on%20my%20reviews%20for%20both%20jobs%20last%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20one%20OEer.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20feel%20guilty%20when%20you're%20doing%20what%20you're%20supposed%20to%20be%20doing.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20way%20to%20know%20exactly%20how%20many%20job%20jugglers%20there%20are.%20In%20September%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fcapabilities%2Fpeople-and-organizational-performance%2Four-insights%2Fsome-employees-are-destroying-value-others-are-building-it-do-you-know-the-difference%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20those%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3Bdouble-dippers%26quot%3B%20constitute%205%25%20of%20a%20typical%20organization's%20staff.%20That%20strikes%20me%20as%20way%20too%20high.%20Last%20quarter%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FLNU02026631%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20estimated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20412%2C000%20Americans%20are%20working%20two%20full-time%20jobs%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20up%20by%20105%2C000%20since%202019.%20Since%20most%20of%20those%20are%20almost%20certainly%20blue-collar%20workers%20struggling%20to%20get%20by%2C%20OE%20professionals%20likely%20comprise%20far%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20the%20white-collar%20workforce.%20It's%20still%20a%20niche%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20think%20the%20bosses%20of%20the%20world%20are%20threatened%20by%20OE%20for%20a%20deeper%20reason%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20goes%20beyond%20the%20numbers.%20There's%20something%20radical%20that%20happens%20to%20a%20worker's%20psychology%20when%20they%20have%20multiple%20jobs.%20If%20your%20company%20is%20putting%20a%20roof%20over%20your%20head%2C%20it's%20hard%20not%20to%20fall%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20hustle-culture%20mentality%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20work%2C%20doing%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20satisfy%20your%20boss.%20That%20dependence%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20big%20mental%20weight%20that%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20carry%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Isaac%2C%20the%20OE%20blogger%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20go%20a%20little%20harder%20because%20they%20have%20to.%26quot%3B%20But%20because%20the%20overemployed%20are%20no%20longer%20wholly%20dependent%20on%20any%20one%20employer%2C%20each%20job%20starts%20to%20look%20a%20little%20more%20disposable%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20if%20we're%20being%20honest%2C%20is%20precisely%20how%20many%20CEOs%20view%20their%20employees.%20On%20the%20forums%2C%20when%20someone%20complains%20about%20being%20unhappy%20at%20their%20J2%20or%20their%20J3%2C%20the%20responses%20pour%20in.%20%3Cem%3ETime%20to%20drop%20that%20shitty%20job%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20they%20say.%20%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20why%20we%20OE%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%20recently%20faced%20such%20a%20dilemma.%20Her%20new%20boss%20at%20her%20J1%20kept%20dumping%20more%20and%20more%20work%20on%20her%2C%20until%20she%20eventually%20found%20herself%20running%20a%20whole%20team%20of%20employees.%20All%20she%20wanted%20was%20a%20promotion%2C%20and%20maybe%20a%20%2410%2C000%20raise%2C%20to%20compensate%20her%20for%20the%20additional%20responsibilities%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20take%20on.%20But%20her%20employer%20refused.%20Before%2C%20she%20would%20have%20stuck%20it%20out%2C%20dependent%20on%20her%20job%20to%20support%20her%20and%20her%20family.%20But%20this%20time%20she%20had%20the%20backup%20of%20a%20great%20J2%2C%20which%20gave%20her%20the%20freedom%20to%20walk%20away.%20When%20she%20quit%2C%20the%20company%20posted%20her%20opening%20as%20a%20manager%20role%20%E2%80%94%20and%20asked%20her%20whether%20she'd%20come%20back%20for%20the%20better%20job%20title%20and%20higher%20pay%20she%20had%20wanted%20all%20along.%20She%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20pervasive%20thing%20in%20my%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20be%20told%2C%20'Hey%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20groom%20you%20to%20promote%20you%2C'%20and%20then%20something%20will%20happen%20and%20that%20promotion%20just%20won't%20come%20through.%20I%20realized%20that%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20improve%20my%20family's%20financial%20health%2C%20I%20was%20going%20to%20have%20to%20take%20a%20different%20tactic%2C%20and%20this%20is%20what%20I%20chose.%26quot%3B%20She%20promised%20her%20husband%20that%20she'll%20take%20it%20easy%20for%20a%20few%20months%20in%20her%20J2%2C%20which%20is%20now%20her%20J1.%20But%20the%20truth%20is%2C%20she's%20already%20started%20scrolling%20through%20job%20postings%20on%20LinkedIn%20and%20Indeed.%20She'll%20start%20applying%20in%20earnest%20in%20the%20new%20year.%20The%20winner%20will%20be%20her%20new%20J2.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-workers-secret-two-multiple-jobs-salaries-tech-tips-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699871581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d5ec53cc84b4dfaffcd94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-workers-secret-two-multiple-jobs-salaries-tech-tips-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22He%20was%20working%20three%20full-time%20jobs%20at%20Meta%2C%20IBM%2C%20and%20Tinder.%20His%20bosses%20didn't%20know.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aito%40businessinsider.com%20(Aki%20Ito)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-workers-secret-two-multiple-jobs-salaries-tech-tips-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Antibiotics%3A%20What%20Would%20a%20Post-Antibiotic%20World%20Look%20Like%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170130%2Fsj-objio-8hHxO3iYuU0-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20much%20about%20being%20able%20to%20access%20a%20course%20of%20antibiotics%20to%20head%20off%20an%20infection.%20But%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20always%20the%20case%20%E2%80%93%20antibiotics%20have%20been%20available%20for%20less%20than%20a%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%2C%20patients%20would%20die%20of%20relatively%20trivial%20infections%20that%20became%20more%20serious.%20Some%20serious%20infections%2C%20such%20as%20those%20involving%20the%20heart%20valves%2C%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F20173297%2F%5C%22%3Einevitably%3C%2Fa%3E%20fatal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20serious%20infections%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3070694%2F%5C%22%3Etuberculosis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20weren%E2%80%99t%20always%20fatal.%20Up%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.biorxiv.org%2Fcontent%2F10.1101%2F729426v1.full.pdf%5C%22%3Ehalf%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20people%20died%20within%20a%20year%20with%20the%20most%20severe%20forms%2C%20but%20some%20people%20recovered%20without%20treatment%20and%20the%20remainder%20had%20ongoing%20chronic%20infection%20that%20slowly%20ate%20away%20at%20the%20body%20over%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20had%20antibiotics%2C%20the%20outcomes%20for%20these%20infections%20were%20much%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20(and%20death)%20before%20antibiotics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%E2%80%99ve%20probably%20heard%20of%20Alexander%20Fleming%E2%80%99s%20accidental%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acs.org%2Feducation%2Fwhatischemistry%2Flandmarks%2Fflemingpenicillin.html%5C%22%3Ediscovery%20of%20penicillin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20fungal%20spores%20landed%20on%20a%20plate%20with%20bacteria%20left%20over%20a%20long%20weekend%20in%201928.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ox.ac.uk%2Fnews%2Fscience-blog%2Fpenicillin-oxford-story%5C%22%3Efirst%20patient%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20receive%20penicillin%20was%20an%20instructive%20example%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20treatment.%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%201941%2C%20Constable%20Albert%20Alexander%20had%20a%20scratch%20on%20his%20face%20that%20had%20become%20infected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20hospitalised%20but%20despite%20various%20treatments%2C%20the%20infection%20progressed%20to%20involve%20his%20head.%20This%20required%20removing%20one%20of%20his%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684313%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIn%201941%2C%20Albert%20Alexander%20was%20hospitalised%20with%20a%20severe%20infection.%20Photo%3A%20Jonathan%20Borba%2FPexels%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHoward%20Florey%2C%20the%20Australian%20pharmacologist%20then%20working%20in%20Oxford%2C%20was%20concerned%20penicillin%20could%20be%20toxic%20in%20humans.%20Therefore%2C%20he%20felt%20it%20was%20only%20ethical%20to%20give%20this%20new%20drug%20to%20a%20patient%20in%20a%20desperate%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConstable%20Alexander%20was%20given%20the%20available%20dose%20of%20penicillin.%20Within%20the%20first%20day%2C%20his%20condition%20had%20started%20to%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20back%20then%2C%20penicillin%20was%20difficult%20to%20produce.%20One%20way%20of%20extending%20the%20limited%20supply%20was%20to%20%E2%80%9Crecycle%E2%80%9D%20penicillin%20that%20was%20excreted%20in%20the%20patient%E2%80%99s%20urine.%20Despite%20this%2C%20supplies%20ran%20out%20by%20the%20fifth%20day%20of%20Alexander%E2%80%99s%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20further%20treatment%2C%20the%20infection%20again%20took%20hold.%20Constable%20Alexander%20eventually%20died%20a%20month%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20now%20face%20a%20world%20where%20we%20are%20potentially%20running%20out%20of%20antibiotics%20%E2%80%93%20not%20because%20of%20difficulties%20manufacturing%20them%2C%20but%20because%20they%E2%80%99re%20losing%20their%20effectiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20we%20use%20antibiotics%20for%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20currently%20use%20antibiotics%20in%20humans%20and%20animals%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons.%20Antibiotics%20reduce%20the%20duration%20of%20illness%20and%20the%20chance%20of%20death%20from%20infection.%20They%20also%20prevent%20infections%20in%20people%20who%20are%20at%20high%20risk%2C%20such%20as%20patients%20undergoing%20surgery%20and%20those%20with%20weakened%20immune%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20antibiotics%20aren%E2%80%99t%20always%20used%20appropriately.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flaninf%2Farticle%2FPIIS1473-3099(20)30084-0%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3EStudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20consistently%20show%20a%20dose%20or%20two%20will%20adequately%20prevent%20infections%20after%20surgery%2C%20but%20antibiotics%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firp.cdn-website.com%2Fd820f98f%2Ffiles%2Fuploaded%2Fsurgical-prophylaxis-prescribing-in-australian-hospitals-results-of-the-2020-surgical-national-antimicrobial-prescribing-survey.pdf%5C%22%3Eoften%3C%2Fa%3E%20continued%20for%20several%20days%20unnecessarily.%20And%20sometimes%20we%20use%20the%20wrong%20type%20of%20antibiotic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firp.cdn-website.com%2Fd820f98f%2Ffiles%2Fuploaded%2Fantimicrobial-prescribing-practice-in-australian-hospitals-results-of-the-2020-hospital-national-antimicrobial-prescribing-survey.pdf%5C%22%3ESurveys%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%2022%25%20of%20antimicrobial%20use%20in%20hospitals%20is%20inappropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684314%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAntibiotics%20are%20used%20for%20longer%20than%20needed%20and%20sometimes%20the%20wrong%20type%20is%20used.%20Photo%3A%20National%20Cancer%20Institute%2FUnsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20situations%2C%20this%20is%20understandable.%20Infections%20in%20different%20body%20sites%20are%20usually%20due%20to%20different%20types%20of%20bacteria.%20When%20the%20diagnosis%20isn%E2%80%99t%20certain%2C%20we%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fresp.13334%5C%22%3Eerr%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20side%20of%20caution%20by%20giving%20broad%20spectrum%20antibiotics%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20have%20active%20treatments%20for%20all%20possible%20infections%2C%20until%20further%20information%20becomes%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20situations%2C%20there%20is%20a%20degree%20of%20inertia.%20If%20the%20patient%20is%20improving%2C%20doctors%20tend%20to%20simply%20continue%20the%20same%20treatment%2C%20rather%20than%20change%20to%20more%20appropriate%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20general%20practice%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20diagnostic%20uncertainty%20and%20therapeutic%20inertia%20are%20often%20magnified.%20Patients%20who%20recover%20after%20starting%20antibiotics%20don%E2%80%99t%20usually%20require%20tests%20or%20come%20back%20for%20review%2C%20so%20there%20is%20no%20easy%20way%20of%20knowing%20if%20the%20antibiotic%20was%20actually%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotic%20prescribing%20can%20be%20more%20complex%20again%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mja.com.au%2Fjournal%2F2014%2F201%2F2%2Fantibiotic-prescribing-practice-residential-aged-care-facilities-health-care%5C%22%3Epatients%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20expecting%20%E2%80%9Ca%20pill%20for%20every%20ill%E2%80%9D.%20While%20doctors%20are%20generally%20good%20at%20educating%20patients%20when%20antibiotics%20are%20not%20likely%20to%20work%20(for%20example%2C%20for%20viral%20infections)%2C%20without%20confirmatory%20tests%20there%20can%20always%20be%20a%20lingering%20doubt%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20both%20doctors%20and%20patients.%20Or%20sometimes%20the%20patient%20goes%20elsewhere%20to%20find%20a%20prescription.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20other%20infections%2C%20resistance%20can%20develop%20if%20treatments%20aren%E2%80%99t%20given%20for%20long%20enough.%20This%20is%20particularly%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F11971765%2F%5C%22%3Ecase%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20tuberculosis%2C%20caused%20by%20a%20slow%20growing%20bacterium%20that%20requires%20a%20particularly%20long%20course%20of%20antibiotics%20to%20cure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20in%20humans%2C%20antibiotics%20are%20also%20used%20to%20prevent%20and%20treat%20infections%20in%20animals.%20However%2C%20a%20proportion%20of%20antibiotics%20are%20used%20for%20growth%20promotion.%20In%20Australia%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mja.com.au%2Fjournal%2F2019%2F211%2F4%2Fantibiotic-use-animals-and-humans-australia%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%2060%25%20of%20antibiotics%20were%20used%20in%20animals%20between%202005-2010%2C%20despite%20growth-promotion%20being%20phased%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20overuse%20a%20problem%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacteria%20become%20resistant%20to%20the%20effect%20of%20antibiotics%20through%20natural%20selection%20%E2%80%93%20those%20that%20survive%20exposure%20to%20antibiotics%20are%20the%20strains%20that%20have%20a%20mechanism%20to%20evade%20their%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20antibiotics%20are%20sometimes%20given%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flaninf%2Farticle%2FPIIS1473-3099(18)30279-2%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Eprevent%3C%2Fa%3E%20recurrent%20urinary%20tract%20infections%2C%20but%20a%20consequence%2C%20any%20infection%20that%20does%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fcid%2Farticle%2F73%2F3%2Fe782%2F6141409%5C%22%3Edevelop%3C%2Fa%3E%20tends%20to%20be%20with%20resistant%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20resistance%20to%20the%20commonly%20used%20first-line%20antibiotics%20occurs%2C%20we%20often%20need%20to%20reach%20deeper%20into%20the%20bag%20to%20find%20other%20effective%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20last-line%20antibiotics%20are%20those%20that%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4202707%2F%5C%22%3Esuperseded%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20had%20serious%20side%20effects%20or%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20given%20conveniently%20as%20tablets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20drugs%20for%20some%20bacteria%20have%20been%20developed%2C%20but%20many%20are%20much%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7955006%2F%5C%22%3Eexpensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20older%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreating%20antibiotics%20as%20a%20valuable%20resource%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20antibiotics%20as%20a%20valuable%20resource%20has%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F8856755%2F%5C%22%3Econcept%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%E2%80%9Cantimicrobial%20stewardship%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20programs%20to%20promote%20the%20responsible%20use%20of%20antibiotics.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20similar%20concept%20to%20environmental%20stewardship%20to%20prevent%20climate%20change%20and%20environmental%20degradation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotics%20are%20a%20rare%20class%20of%20medication%20where%20treatment%20of%20one%20patient%20can%20potentially%20affect%20the%20outcome%20of%20other%20patients%2C%20through%20the%20transmission%20of%20antibiotic%20resistant%20bacteria.%20Therefore%2C%20like%20efforts%20to%20combat%20climate%20change%2C%20antibiotic%20stewardship%20relies%20on%20changing%20individual%20actions%20to%20benefit%20the%20broader%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20climate%20change%2C%20antibiotic%20resistance%20is%20a%20complex%20problem%20when%20seen%20in%20a%20broader%20context.%20Studies%20have%20linked%20resistance%20to%20the%20values%20and%20priorities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flanplh%2Farticle%2FPIIS2542-5196(18)30186-4%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Eof%20governments%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20corruption%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20the%20availability%20of%20electricity%20and%20public%20services.%20This%20highlights%20that%20there%20are%20broader%20%E2%80%9Ccauses%20of%20the%20causes%E2%80%9D%2C%20such%20as%20public%20spending%20on%20sanitation%20and%20health%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fjac%2Farticle%2F74%2F9%2F2803%2F5512029%3Flogin%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Estudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20suggested%20individuals%20need%20to%20be%20considered%20within%20the%20broader%20social%20and%20institutional%20influences%20on%20prescribing%20behaviour.%20Like%20all%20human%20behaviour%2C%20antibiotic%20prescribing%20is%20complicated%2C%20and%20factors%20like%20what%20doctors%20feel%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnormal%E2%80%9D%20prescribing%2C%20whether%20junior%20staff%20feel%20they%20can%20challenge%20senior%20doctors%2C%20and%20even%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2016%2F10%2F07%2Fupshot%2Fyour-surgeon-is-probably-a-republican-your-psychiatrist-probably-a-democrat.html%5C%22%3Epolitical%20views%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20be%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20issues%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Finternational-journal-of-technology-assessment-in-health-care%2Farticle%2Fvalue-assessment-of-antimicrobials-and-the-implications-for-development-access-and-funding-of-effective-treatments-australian-stakeholder-perspective%2FD45758CFB95520DA4FF06E46135E0628%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20developing%20new%20antibiotics.%20When%20a%20new%20antibiotic%20is%20first%20approved%20for%20use%2C%20the%20first%20reaction%20for%20prescribers%20is%20not%20to%20use%20it%2C%20whether%20to%20ensure%20it%20retains%20its%20effectiveness%20or%20because%20it%20is%20often%20very%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20really%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fcid%2Farticle%2F50%2F8%2F1081%2F449089%3Flogin%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Eencourage%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20development%20of%20new%20antibiotics%2C%20particularly%20when%20pharma%20research%20and%20development%20budgets%20can%20easily%20be%20diverted%20to%20developing%20drugs%20for%20conditions%20patients%20take%20for%20years%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20slow%20moving%20pandemic%20of%20resistance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20fail%20to%20act%2C%20we%20are%20looking%20at%20an%20almost%20unthinkable%20scenario%20where%20antibiotics%20no%20longer%20work%20and%20we%20are%20cast%20back%20into%20the%20dark%20ages%20of%20medicine%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famr-review.org%2F%5C%22%3EDavid%20Cameron%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20former%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotic%20resistance%20is%20already%20a%20problem.%20Almost%20all%20infectious%20diseases%20physicians%20have%20had%20the%20dreaded%20call%20about%20patients%20with%20infections%20that%20were%20essentially%20untreatable%2C%20or%20where%20they%20had%20to%20scramble%20to%20find%20supplies%20of%20long-forgotten%20last-line%20antibiotics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20already%20hospitals%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20that%20have%20had%20to%20carefully%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reactgroup.org%2Fnews-and-views%2Fnews-and-opinions%2Fyear-2022%2Fthe-impact-of-antibiotic-resistance-on-cancer-treatment-especially-in-low-and-middle-income-countries-and-the-way-forward%2F%5C%22%3Econsider%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20viable%20to%20treat%20cancers%2C%20because%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6276316%2F%5C%22%3Ehigh%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20infections%20with%20antibiotic-resistant%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20global%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(21)02724-0%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20in%202019%2C%20almost%205%20million%20deaths%20occurred%20with%20an%20infection%20involving%20antibiotic-resistant%20bacteria.%20Some%201.3%20million%20would%20not%20have%20occurred%20if%20the%20bacteria%20were%20not%20resistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%E2%80%99s%202014%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famr-review.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FAMR%2520Review%2520Paper%2520-%2520Tackling%2520a%2520crisis%2520for%2520the%2520health%2520and%2520wealth%2520of%2520nations_1.pdf%5C%22%3EO%E2%80%99Neill%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20predicted%20deaths%20from%20antimicrobial%20resistance%20could%20rise%20to%2010%20million%20deaths%20each%20year%2C%20and%20cost%202-3.5%25%20of%20global%20GDP%2C%20by%202050%20based%20on%20trends%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20can%20we%20do%20about%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20lot%20we%20can%20do%20to%20prevent%20antibiotic%20resistance.%20We%20can%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%