ing%20the%20waters%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20including%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%2C%20to%20enable%20extensive%20submarine%20operations%20across%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20naval%20assets%20docked%20in%20Karachi%20include%20a%20Type%20039%20diesel-electric%20submarine.%20While%20the%20precise%20capability%20of%20this%20submarine%2C%20including%20how%20quiet%20it%20is%2C%20are%20closely%20held%20Naval%20secrets%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20boat%20in%20the%20waters%20of%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%2C%20showcase%20Beijing's%20confidence%20in%20being%20able%20to%20deploy%20Naval%20assets%20several%20thousand%20kilometres%20away%20from%20their%20homeports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Chinese%20Type-52D%20guided%20missile%20destroyer%20along%20with%20two%20Type-54%20frigates%20docked%20at%20Karachi%20ahead%20of%20nine-day%20Sea%20Guardian-3%20naval%20exercises.%20(high%20res%3A%20here)%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Chinese%20Type-52D%20guided%20missile%20destroyer%20along%20with%20two%20Type-54%20frigates%20docked%20at%20Karachi%20ahead%20of%20nine-day%20Sea%20Guardian-3%20naval%20exercises.%20(high%20res%3A%20here)%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Ffpn6qe1o_karachi-port_625x300_13_November_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChinese%20Type-52D%20guided%20missile%20destroyer%20along%20with%20two%20Type-54%20frigates%20docked%20at%20Karachi%20ahead%20of%20nine-day%20Sea%20Guardian-3%20naval%20exercises.%20(high%20res%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fd5ahs6s_karachi-port_625x300_13_November_23.jpg%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20eighth%20time%20since%20the%20Chinese%20PLAN%20(People's%20Liberation%20Army%20Navy)%20deployed%20a%20submarine%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20since%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20also%20known%20to%20have%20operated%20nuclear-powered%20fast%20attack%20submarines%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean.%20These%20can%2C%20theoretically%2C%20remain%20indefinitely%20submerged%20since%20they%20do%20not%20need%20to%20surface%20other%20than%20to%20replenish%20supplies%20onboard.%20It%20is%20unclear%20if%20a%20Chinese%20nuclear%20submarine%20has%20also%20been%20deployed%20with%20the%20Chinese%20fleet%20taking%20part%20in%20these%20exercises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20monitoring%20the%20deployment%20of%20Chinese%20warships%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20for%20the%20Sea%20Guardian%20exercises%20say%20the%20Type-039%20submarine%20and%20its%20accompanying%20support%20ship%20were%20regularly%20tracked%20by%20Navy%20P8%20reconnaissance%20aircraft%20after%20they%20entered%20the%20region%20through%20the%20Malacca%20straits.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20sources%20point%20out%2C%20is%20a%20prelude%20to%20what%20may%20emerge%20in%20the%20future%20of%20a%20greater%20Chinese%20presence%20in%20the%20region.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20question%20of%20if%20but%20when%20China%20decides%20to%20deploy%20a%20carrier%20battle%20group%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20region%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20say.%20With%20its%20existing%20port%20facilities%2C%20including%20its%20first%20overseas%20base%20in%20Djibouti%2C%20berthing%20an%20aircraft%20carrier%20and%20its%20accompanying%20battle-group%20will%20not%20pose%20a%20logistical%20hurdle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%202015%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20government%20agreed%20to%20purchase%20eight%20variants%20of%20the%20Type%20039%20submarines%20in%20a%20deal%20reportedly%20worth%20%245%20billion.%20Four%20of%20the%20submarines%20were%20expected%20to%20be%20built%20by%20the%20Karachi%20Shipyard%20%26amp%3B%20Engineering%20Works.%20None%20of%20the%20submarines%20have%20been%20delivered%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EVessel%20YANGCHENGHU%20a%20suspected%20PLA%20NAVY%20TYPE%20926%20Submarine%20Support%20Vessel%2C%20is%20currently%20approaching%20Karachi%2C%20it%20was%20tracked%20from%20China's%20Hainan%20Naval%20base%20%26amp%3B%20is%20likely%20en-route%20to%20Pakistan%20for%20the%20upcoming%20China-Pakistan%20Joint%20Naval%20Drills%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F04vJQY4reF%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F04vJQY4reF%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Damien%20Symon%20(%40detresfa_)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdetresfa_%2Fstatus%2F1722227576238944733%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%208%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESatellite%20images%20with%20NDTV%20indicate%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20Chinese%20Type%20926%20submarine%20tender%20docked%20in%20Karachi.%20One%20of%20three%20ships%20of%20this%20class%20believed%20to%20be%20in%20service%20with%20the%20Chinese%20Navy%2C%20the%20Type%20926%20replenishes%20submarines%20and%20is%20capable%20of%20rescuing%20a%20submarine%20in%20distress.%20The%20presence%20of%20this%20ship%20is%20a%20giveaway%20to%20the%20presence%20of%20Chinese%20submarines%20in%20the%20vicinity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20battle-group%20also%20includes%20a%20Type%2052D%20destroyer%2C%20two%20Type%2054%20frigates%20and%20a%20Type%20903%20Replenishment%20Oiler%20which%20enables%20the%20warships%20and%20submarine%20to%20sustain%20long-range%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20planners%20and%20decision-makers%20have%20to%20squarely%20face%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Chinese%20have%20vital%20interests%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20-%20specifically%20its%20sea%20lanes%20which%20carry%20most%20of%20China's%20energy%2C%20trade%2C%20raw%20materials%20and%20finished%20goods.%20Consequently%2C%20we%20are%20going%20to%20see%20the%20increasing%20presence%20of%20PLA%20Navy%20(PLAN)%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%3B%20warships%20as%20well%20as%20submarines.%20Neither%20their%20presence%20on%20the%20high%20seas%2C%20nor%20their%20putting%20into%20(friendly)%20ports%20is%20something%20that%20we%20can%20take%20exception%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20said%C2%A0former%20Navy%20chief%20Admiral%20Arun%20Prakash%20(retd).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20China%20has%20created%20enough%20maritime%20footholds%2C%20right%20across%20the%20IOR%20-%20what%20was%20termed%20a%20%26quot%3Bstring%20of%20pearls%26quot%3B%20-%20but%20was%20actually%20a%20series%20of%20friendly%20ports%20financed%20by%20China%20-%20which%20could%20be%20used%20by%20the%20PLA%20Navy%20as%20and%20when%20required.%20In%202016%2C%20China%20established%20its%20first%20overseas%20military%20base%20in%20Djibouti%2C%20and%20more%20will%20follow%20-%20perhaps%20in%20Africa.%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Orange%20shipping%20containers%20restrict%20access%20to%20areas%20where%20Chinese%20warships%20are%20docked%20at%20Karachi%20port.%20(high%20res%3A%20here)%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Orange%20shipping%20containers%20restrict%20access%20to%20areas%20where%20Chinese%20warships%20are%20docked%20at%20Karachi%20port.%20(high%20res%3A%20here)%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2F4aoqdhco_karachi-port_625x300_13_November_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrange%20shipping%20containers%20restrict%20access%20to%20areas%20where%20Chinese%20warships%20are%20docked%20at%20Karachi%20port.%20(high%20res%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fl5k3d9cg_karachi-port_625x300_13_November_23.jpg%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%20this%20year%2C%20Navy%20Chief%20Admiral%20R%20Hari%20Kumar%20said%20that%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20is%20''keeping%20a%20watch''%20on%20the%20deployment%20of%20Chinese%20Naval%20assets%20to%20Pakistani%20Ports.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20large%20presence%20of%20Chinese%20vessels.%20At%20any%20point%20of%20time%2C%20there%20are%20three%20to%20six%20Chinese%20warships%20in%20the%20India%20Ocean%20Region%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20China%20also%20deploys%20research%20vessels%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20tracking%20Chinese%20Naval%20assets%20is%20a%20constant%20effort%20for%20the%20Indian%20Navy.%20Chinese%20vessels%20sail%20west%20to%20enter%20the%20waters%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20through%20key%20choke%20points%2C%20the%20straits%20of%20Malacca%2C%20Lombok%20or%20the%20Sunda%20Straits.%20Indian%20Navy%20P-8%20maritime%20reconnaissance%20aircraft%20and%20mission-deployed%20warships%20are%20frequently%20positioned%20to%20intercept%20Chinese%20vessels%20and%20track%20their%20movements%20for%20extended%20periods%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tracking%20the%20movement%20of%20Chinese%20warships%2C%20India%20works%20closely%20with%20the%20United%20States%2C%20a%20key%20maritime%20partner%2C%20often%20for%20real-time%20intelligence.%20Just%20last%20week%2C%20at%20the%202%2B2%20dialogue%20in%20New%20Delhi%20between%20Foreign%20and%20Defence%20Ministers%2C%20both%20sides%20''underlined%20their%20strong%20commitment%20to%20safeguarding%20a%20free%2C%20open%2C%20and%20inclusive%20Indo-Pacific%2C''%20a%20veiled%20reference%20to%20China%20which%20bases%20its%20economic%20expansion%20through%20its%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%2C%20an%20international%20infrastructure%20development%20strategy%20adopted%20by%20Beijing%20in%202013%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20investing%20in%20more%20than%20150%20countries.%20Beijing%20backs%20the%20Initiative%20through%20an%20increasingly%20robust%20maritime%20presence%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20announcing%20its%20investment%20of%20more%20than%20%24500%20million%20in%20the%20Colombo%20Port%20Terminal%20being%20developed%20by%20the%20Adani%20Group%20on%20November%208%2C%20Washing