%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntended%20as%20a%20homage%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FGreatest-Generation%5C%22%3Egreatest%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20film%20begins%20with%20an%20old%20soldier%20(the%20titular%20Private%20Ryan)%20searching%20the%20graves%20in%20the%20vast%20American%20military%20cemetery%20overlooking%20Omaha%20Beach%20in%20Normandy.%20This%20was%20the%20scene%20of%20some%20of%20the%20deadliest%20fighting%20on%20June%206%201944.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinding%20the%20grave%20he%20is%20looking%20for%2C%20the%20aged%20veteran%20drops%20to%20his%20knees%20before%20the%20camera%20zooms%20in%20on%20his%20eyes%20so%20that%20Spielberg%20can%20take%20us%20back%20to%20the%20battle%20on%20that%20grey%20spring%20morning.%20It%20is%20a%20powerful%20scene%2C%20and%20it%20has%20clearly%20inspired%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Escaper%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20director%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.co.uk%2Farticles%2Ftheres-a-lot-of-deep-deep-feeling-director-oliver-parker-on-his-new-film-the-great-escaper%5C%22%3EOliver%20Parker%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20shadow%20of%20%3Cem%3ESaving%20Private%20Ryan%3C%2Fem%3E%20looms%20large%20throughout.%20Like%20Spielberg%2C%20Parker%20takes%20us%20back%20to%20a%20Normandy%20burial%20ground%2C%20this%20time%20the%20Commonwealth%20War%20Graves%20Commission%20Cemetery%20in%20the%20town%20of%20Bayeux.%20He%20has%20us%20wander%20among%20the%20serried%20ranks%20of%20headstones%20and%2C%20via%20a%20series%20of%20flashbacks%2C%20we%20witness%20the%20carnage%20on%20the%20coast%20in%20washed-out%20colour%2C%20with%20the%20salt%20and%20sea%20spray%20in%20our%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20similarities%2C%20I%20think%2C%20reveal%20the%20ultimate%20point%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Escaper%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Through%20the%20familiar%20trope%20of%20a%20war-damaged%20British%20veteran%2C%20the%2